Text:
Seperti yg sedia maklum, buka je rentas negeri, majoriti online sales drop. Aku pun drop 50% in sales dgn amount spending ada yg sama. Ya, roas aku below breakeven.

Sales revenue kilang aku mostly bergantung kpd online sales since april 2020
Translated Text:
As is well known, just open across the country, the majority of online sales drop. I also dropped 50% in sales with the same amount of spending there. Yes, I'm sorry below break even.

My factory's sales revenue has mostly depended on online sales since April 2020

Text:
Tapi kami still survive kerana masih ada retail distribution.

Semua org dok cerita online distribution. Hari ni aku nak kongsi apa yg aku dah buat utk retail distribution.
Translated Text:
But we still survive because there is still retail distribution.

Everyone is talking about online distribution. Today I want to share what I have done for retail distribution.

Text:
Hal no. 1 mengenai retail distribution is to decide market price on ur product. Kesilapan usahawan melayu bila jual kepada peruncit ialah hanya set harga “tolak kedai”. 

Ini kesilapan awal kami. Tolak kedai, tolak kat org ni, tolak kat org tu.
Translated Text:
Item no. 1 regarding retail distribution is to decide market price on ur product. The mistake Malay entrepreneurs make when selling to retailers is to only set the price "tolak kedai".

This is our initial mistake. Push the shop, push this person, push that person.

Text:
Apa akibatnya? Margin usahawan pengilang terlalu kecil, tidak adil dan akan spark price war between retailers or agent.

Sebaiknya set siap2 RSP. Retail Selling Price.

Mcm mana nk set RSP? Set after u compare ur product value/usp VS harga pesaing and their strength.
Translated Text:
What were the consequences? Manufacturers' margins are too small, unfair and will spark price wars between retailers or agents.

We recommend that you set RSP ready. Retail Selling Price.

How do you want to set the RSP? Set after u compare ur product value/usp VS competitor's price and their strength.

Text:
So dah set RSP, whats next?

Identify these 3 things:

1. Factory margin (you)
2. Distributor Margin
3. Retail margin

Margin ni semua based on ur RSP.
For me the best margin percentage is 50% on factory, 15-20% on distributor and 30-35% on retail
Translated Text:
So dah set RSP, whats next?

Identify these 3 things:

1. Factory margin (you)
2. Distributor Margin
3. Retail margin

Margin ni semua based on ur RSP.
For me the best margin percentage is 50% on factory, 15-20% on distributor and 30-35% on retail

u see. all this life punching u anytime.

be strong.

be strong.

- Broad targeting (literally x target apa2, semua default)
- Interest stack (ikutlah produk tu niche apa)
- Lookalike (perencah sesedap rasa)
- Retargeting (complete the cycle)

- Broad targeting (literally x any target, all default)
- Interest stack (follow what niche the product is)
- Lookalike (flavor as delicious as the taste)
- Retargeting (complete the cycle)

Text:
Pastu, boss lama kat kuantan panggil balik utk tlg bisnes dorg. Aku dlm keadaan terdesak maka pulanglah ke kampung halaman utk bekerja. Tapi aku tanam dlm diri aku, one day aku akan kembali dlm dunia bisnes.

Dlm 1 tahun lebih aku kerja kat kuantan tu, atok sedare aku ada bagi..
Translated Text:
Well, the old boss in Kuantan called me back for more business. I'm in a desperate situation so I go back to my hometown to work. But I planted in myself, one day I will return to the business world.

In the more than 1 year I have been working in Kuantan, my grandfather knew I was there for..

Text: Mesin buat mee 😂😂 maka mula perjalanan bisnes keluarga kami yg pertama! Atok sedare mintak tlg supply mee utk dia je, but we got it to another level sikit la, kita buat branding, kita dptkan bengkel utk proses mee, klu x hari2 buat mee kat dapur, bunyi bukan senyap XD https://t.co/HOv8JOsI8s
Translated Text: Noodle making machine 😂😂 and so begins our first family business journey! Atok already asked me to supply the noodles for him, but we got it to another level a little bit, we did branding, we got a workshop to process the noodles, even if you make noodles in the kitchen every day, the noise is not silent XD https://t.co /HOv8JOsI8s

Text:
Level ni baru aku experience distribution channel & logistik dlm bisnes.

Aku manage approach 14 tmpt utk ‘subscribe’ mee kuning. Aku xde pengalaman xde ilmu, jadi aku terjah.

“Berminat nk jual mee kuning kami? Mee kuning kami xde bahan pengawet, harga RM 1, boleh jual RM1.50” https://t.co/0mJt0tH8z8
Translated Text:
At this level, I just experienced channel distribution & logistics in business.

I manage approach 14 times to 'subscribe' to mee kuning. I have no experience and no knowledge, so I'm stuck.

"Interested in selling our yellow noodles? Our yellow noodles have no preservatives, the price is RM1, you can sell them for RM1.50" https://t.co/0mJt0tH8z8

Text:
Alhamdulillah, kedai yg nk terima tu ada yg smpi skarang kami masih supply, ada yg aku down teruk, sbb ad kta dia xnk jual mee aku sbb dia nk jual 1 jenama je. Aiyoyo. Xpelah.

Kuantan bkn kecik, aku boleh spend masa 8 jam cover 1 part of kuantan utk hantar mee. Mee tahan 3 hari.
Translated Text:
Alhamdulillah, the store that wants to accept it has some that until now we are still supplying, some that I'm down badly, because he said he won't sell my noodles because he only wants to sell 1 brand. Aiyoyo Xpelah.

Kuantan is not small, I can spend 8 hours covering 1 part of Kuantan to deliver noodles. Noodles last 3 days.

Text: Hari kedua dah nk amik return dan collect duit. Ada kedai laku habis jual, ada kedai sayup kdg xjual semua, rosak semua. Ada Yg rosak tu kita ganti sbb kedai bayar cash, ada yg rosak tu mmg ganti bodoh je klu kedai tu buat bayar consignment (bayar apa yg terjual)
Translated Text: On the second day, I'm going to return and collect the money. There are shops that are sold out, there are shops that sell everything, everything is damaged. Some of the damaged ones we replace as the store pays cash, some of the damaged ones are just stupidly replaced if the store pays consignment (pay for what is sold)

Text:
Disebabkan mee tahan 3 hari, distribution limited ke 3 part of kuantan shj. Kuantan ada byk part. Klu org kuantan, dia faham apa maksud aku. Aku buat route.

kat sini sales terganggu. Xboleh expand territory. And production under capacity sgt2
Translated Text:
Because the noodles last 3 days, distribution is limited to 3 parts of Kuantan only. Kuantan has many parts. Kuantan people, he understands what I mean. I made a route.

here sales are interrupted. X can expand territory. And production is very under capacity

Text:
What do u do if u at my shoes? Aku share my thought process masa tu.

- untung 1 paket mee, 20 sen
- mesin kecik, dpt geran hanya mampu upgrade speed shj
- mee lepas 3 hari berkulat dan mmg xnk tambah pengawet atau ubah resepi
Translated Text:
What do you do if you are in my shoes? I share my thought process at that time.

- win 1 packet of noodles, 20 cents
- small machine, can only get a grant to upgrade the speed
- the noodles become moldy after 3 days and do not add preservatives or change the recipe

Text:
So aku fikir masa tu, utk tingkatkan distribution, kena tingkatkan 2 perkara

- shelf life kena pertingkatkan jadi seminggu dua minggu
- production at cap and growing

Aku fikir xboleh jadi mmg kena bg mee tahan lama tanpa pengawet klu tidak mmg gg xde motivasi, tutup bisnes..
Translated Text:
So I think at that time, to increase distribution, you have to increase 2 things

- shelf life has to be increased to a week or two
- production at cap and growing

I think it may be necessary to make long-lasting noodles without preservatives, otherwise there is no motivation, close the business..

Text:
We eksperimen A LOT. Byk cara nk preserve mee

- letak mee dlm peti sejuk
(problem: org kuantan xbiasa cari mee kat peti sejuk, dan kebykkn kedai peti sejuk dah penuh, malah ada yg xde peti sejuk)
- bekukn mee (same problem)
- letak pengawet (tetttt)
Translated Text:
We experiment A LOT. There are many ways to preserve noodles

- put the noodles in the fridge
(problem: people in Kuantan are not used to looking for noodles in the refrigerator, and most of the refrigerator stores are full, and some don't even have a refrigerator)
- freeze noodles (same problem)
- put preservative (tetttt)

Text:
Sbg salah seorg pelajar kurang cemerlang bacelor food sains, aku ingat kelas preservation makanan, dan ada lagi satu cara nak bg mee panjang umur

✨Pengeringan✨

Aku bg idea ni kat bapak aku, dia setuju cuma dia xpasti mcm mana prosesnya.

Dipendekkan cerita aku kena hijrah
Translated Text:
As one of the less brilliant students in the Bachelor of Food Science, I remember the food preservation class, and there is another way to give noodles a long life.

✨Drying✨

I gave this idea to my father, he agreed, but he was not sure how the process would be.

In short, I had to migrate

Text:

Dkat sinilah titik bermula segalanya yg bentuk aku smpi hari ni. Reference komik one piece: luffy & team berpisah https://t.co/VZQO0gSEK1

Text:

We are happy. Tp lpas tu tukar nama jadi mee sanggul. Sbb konfius dgn muar punya https://t.co/Lql4Q3DbPp

Text:

to penetrate online market XD

so on June 2019 aku launch satu iklan bawah page yg aku buat santai2, Kedai Mukmin.

Buat video iklan, copywriting..tp xde org pm..

Text:
Here is how I navigate the under-reporting problem

Klu korg tak perasan. Dkat dashboard ads manager korang, all the figures tu aku kerat jari sama ada underreporting atau overreporting.

And it goes on and on everyday. Although sblum ios14.5 pun mmg underreporting tp tak teruk.
Translated Text:
Here is how I navigate the under-reporting problem

You didn't notice. In your ads manager's dashboard, all the figures are either underreporting or overreporting.

And it goes on and on everyday. Although before iOS14.5 it was underreporting but not bad.

Text:
So how u navigate this? cmne nk optimize, nk scale dan nk tau result split test?

💋Custom metrics💄

Aku ada formula-formula yg aku cuba dan guna. Namun ada satu formula ni aku rasa paling legit utk digunakan.

Namun ini bukan 100% tepat, but can get close enough
Translated Text:
So how do u navigate this? how do you want to optimize, want to scale and want to know the results of the split test?

💋Custom metrics💄

I have formulas that I tried and used. However, there is one formula that I feel is the most legit to use.

But this is not 100% correct, but can get close enough

Text:
Aku belajar formula ni pun dr satu tweet yg aku nmpk. so i just reshare free value that i got. and it kinda help me.

So bagi yang beginner, jangan terkujat apa yang aku nk tulis ni. slow2 belajar ye.

Yg pertama aku akan tuliskan mcm mana nk access ke Custom metric dlm dashboard
Translated Text:
I learned this formula from one tweet that I saw. so i just share the free value that i got. and it kinda help me.

So for those who are beginners, don't worry about what I want to write. slow2 learn ya.

First, I will write down how to access Custom metrics on the dashboard

Text:
First skali klik ikut step dibwh

1) Column (yg ada list performance, setup etc)
2) Customize Columns
3) Create Custom Metric (sebelah search box)

Anda akan nampak rupa ini

Sebelum masukkn formula, pastikan korg tahu AOV 7days korang berapa. Penting. https://t.co/b5LSROpVh2
Translated Text:
First, click and follow the steps above

1) Column (which has a list of performance, setup etc)
2) Customize Columns
3) Create Custom Metric (next to the search box)

You will see something like this

Before entering the formula, make sure you know your AOV 7 days. Important. https://t.co/b5LSROpVh2

Text:
Klu beginner yg baca ni AOV bermaksud Jumlah Purata Pembelian Pelanggan. Cara nk dpt, mudah je

AOV = Sales/No. of Order

AOV ni watak penting ye.

Dikatakan fb ads ni menggunakan modelled data, dan antara byk2 modelled data di fb ads, yg hampir tepat ialah No. of Purchase.
Translated Text:
If you are a beginner reading this, AOV means the average number of customer purchases. How to get it, it's easy

AOV = Sales/No. of Order

AOV is an important character, isn't it?

It is said that this fb ad uses modeled data, and between the many modeled data on fb ads, the one that is almost correct is No. of Purchase.

Text:
So kita ambil kesempatan terhadap modelled data Purchase ni dan masukkan ke dalam formula

Purchase x (AOV) = Purchase Conversion Value

Notice changes yg aku buat kat custom metrics dibawah. Format Currency.

Dan anda akan dpt jumlah sales hampir benar dlm dashboard korang https://t.co/MVdZrJG4IV
Translated Text:
So let's take this opportunity to model Purchase data and enter it into the formula

Purchase x (AOV) = Purchase Conversion Value

Notice the changes that I made in custom metrics below. Currency Formats.

And you will get almost correct sales numbers on your dashboard https://t.co/MVdZrJG4IV

Text:
Kemudian kita nak cari Modelled ROAS

Formula tambah sikit (purchase X AOV korg)/Amount Spent

So dari sini korg akan dpt bacaan ROAS hampir benar dkat dkat dashboard korang https://t.co/rhlRHPk3FI
Translated Text:
Then we want to find Modeled ROAS

Formula add a little (purchase X AOV korg)/Amount Spent

So from here you will get an almost correct ROAS reading on your dashboard https://t.co/rhlRHPk3FI

Text:
So lepas ni lebih mudah korang nk dptkan clarity ttg apa yg jadi kat spending dan return fb ads korang.

Lebih better kalau korg boleh compare, result yg fb bg dgn result yg korg kira, dan tgk perbezaannya.

Disclaimer: ni utk dptkn bacaan bg bisnes E-Commerce ye.

Moga membantu.
Translated Text:
So after this, it will be easier for you to get clarity about what is happening with your spending and return fb ads.

It would be better if you could compare the result that FB gave you with the result you calculated, and see the difference.

Disclaimer: this is to get reading for your E-Commerce business.

May it help.

Text:
Drpd buku Profit First by Mike Michalowicz, silapnya ialah setiap kali dapat jualan sahaja, biz owner jarang yg ✨ASINGKAN PROFIT✨ keluar dulu.

Dlm kepala fikir, ada la profit tu dlm akaun bank, xpe bayar je dlu expenses yg diperlukan. Sampailah akaun kering = profit hilang https://t.co/TWvVT1fx7T
Translated Text:
From the book Profit First by Mike Michalowicz, the mistake is that every time they get a sale, the biz owner who ✨SEPARATE PROFIT✨ comes out first.

In my head I thought, there is that profit in the bank account, just pay the necessary expenses. Dry account = lost profit https://t.co/TWvVT1fx7T

Text:
Saya sendiri alami situasi tu masa awal2 jual mee sanggul online. Mmg garu kepala, rasa kenapa duit hilang, celah mana bocor, cashflow lari, dah rupa gali lubang sana utk tutup lubang sini.

Pening kepala saya fikir, sampai bila nk gali tutup lubang ni. Panadol pun xleh setel. https://t.co/wcCnanxICJ
Translated Text:
I personally experienced that situation when I first sold bun noodles online. I'm scratching my head, wondering why the money is missing, where are the gaps leaking, cash flow running away, it looks like they're digging a hole there to cover this hole.

I'm dizzy thinking, until when I'm going to dig and cover this hole. Even Panadol can be adjusted. https://t.co/wcCnanxICJ

Text:
Segalanya berubah bila saya asingkan profit dlu.

Ini yg sy dah amalkan & korang perlu buat perkara yg sama. Gabungan amalan ilmu Mike + Basit. Basit panggil Divide and Conquer.

Apa mazhab ni? Ia ialah teknik kage bunshin no jutsu akaun bank korang kepada 5 bank akaun (optimum) https://t.co/buHBzKJCo9
Translated Text:
Everything changed when I separated the profit first.

This is what I have practiced & you need to do the same thing. A combination of Mike + Basit knowledge practice. Basit calls it Divide and Conquer.

What is this sect? It's a kage bunshin no jutsu technique of your bank account to 5 bank accounts (optimum) https://t.co/buHBzKJCo9

Text:
Saya akan cerita 3 mazhab dlm teknik yg sama. 1 mazhab mike, mazhab basit, dan mazhab saya XD haha

😎Mike
Akaun Pertama - Akaun Pendapatan; akaun khas utk menerima hasil jualan. The only money out dalam akaun ni ialah ke akaun2 yg dah dipisahkan. Apa akaun2 tu? Let's Jom! https://t.co/Iq82n7cB0p
Translated Text:
I will tell 3 sects in the same technique. 1 mike's sect, basit's sect, and my sect XD haha

😎Mike
First Account - Income Account; special account to receive sales revenue. The only money out in this account is to accounts that have been separated. What are those accounts? Let's Go! https://t.co/Iq82n7cB0p

Text:
Akaun kedua Mike - Akaun Profit; Mike nasihatkan untuk korang asingkan 1%-15% profit daripada revenue every 14 days masuk dlm akaun profit. Duit dlam ni disimpan dgn tujuan

1) Kumpul 2-3 bulan cash reserve
2) Owner withdraw every 3 month
3) Growth/Expansion
4) Investment https://t.co/MBQK7Xymvn
Translated Text:
Mike's second account - Profit Account; Mike advises you to set aside 1%-15% profit from revenue every 14 days into the profit account. This money is kept with a purpose

1) Collect 2-3 months cash reserve
2) Owner withdraw every 3 months
3) Growth/Expansion
4) Investment https://t.co/MBQK7Xymvn

Text: Akaun ketiga Mike -  Akaun utk gaji business owner..Yang ni klu korg, kira akaun personal korang la gamaknya. https://t.co/CX4aek14Dt
Translated Text: Mike's third account - An account for the business owner's salary. https://t.co/CX4aek14Dt

Text:
Akaun keempat ialah utk akaun utk bayar cukai
dan kelima ialah akaun OPEX.

So kat sini jelas yang Mike fokus on asingkan duit sales ke dalam akaun2 lain dlu, barulah akaun OPEX yg terakhir. and he works with whatever budget left in the OPEX account.
Translated Text:
The fourth account is for an account to pay taxes
and the fifth is the OPEX account.

So here it is clear that Mike focuses on allocating sales money into other accounts first, then the OPEX account last. and he works with whatever budget is left in the OPEX account.

Text:
Secara ringkasnya, mazhab basit rupa begini:

1) Akaun Opex (bayar gaji etc)
2) Akaun Management (bayaran tahunan spt cukai, lesen, roadtax, audit dsb)
3) Akaun Cash Reserve (Le profit, emergency, investment)
4) Akaun development (Training, course)
5) Akaun Fun (bonus, dine out)
Translated Text:
In a nutshell, the basic school looks like this:

1) Opex account (pay salary etc)
2) Management Account (annual payment such as tax, license, roadtax, audit etc.)
3) Cash Reserve Account (Le profit, emergency, investment)
4) Development account (Training, course)
5) Fun Account (bonus, dine out)

Text:
Dan saya selaku biz owner level marhaen, hanya buat 2 akaun sahaja (means korang yg baru nk mula, xperlu rasa overwhelm nk kena buat 5)

1) akaun maybank as akaun income, cash reserve, and profit
2) akaun CIMB as OPEX. kenapa CIMB, sbb CIMB ada debit card.
Translated Text:
And I, as a biz owner at the advanced level, only make 2 accounts (meaning those of you who are just starting out, don't feel overwhelmed by having to make 5)

1) maybank account as income, cash reserve, and profit account
2) CIMB account as OPEX. why CIMB, because CIMB has a debit card.

Text:
Walaupun begitu, mungkin aku akan ada adjustment sikit dlm pengaturannya. apa dia adjustment tersebut?

Belum dpt ilham lagi. sbb ada part CIMB efisyen, dan ada part Maybank efisyen.
Translated Text:
Even so, maybe I will have a little adjustment in the arrangement. what is the adjustment?

Not inspired yet. as there is an efficient CIMB part, and there is an efficient Maybank part.

Text:
So style yg mana sesuai utk korang? Style Mike ke, style basit ke, atau style simple je cm aku?

Share sikit pendapat korang biz owner yg baru nk mula atau dah 3-5 tahun dlm biz, cmne cara korang manage cashflow bisnes.

Manalah ramai nk belajar. Ini ilmu rare dan ramai silap.
Translated Text:
So which style is right for you? Is it Mike's style, is it basic style, or is it just my simple style?

Share some of your thoughts, business owners who are just starting out or have been in the business for 3-5 years, how do you manage business cashflow.

Where many people want to learn. This is rare knowledge and there are many mistakes.

Text:
Dlm klip di atas aku mention bluetick ni, most of the time adalah disebabkan 

1) kau salah audience
2) Audience xdpt jawapan soalan subconcious dlm kepala dorg

nombor 1 tu, mudah je nk setel, kau test je audience lain..tapi kalau test audience lain pun, semedang bluetick acano?
Translated Text:
In the clip above I mentioned this bluetick, most of the time it is caused

1) you have the wrong audience
2) The audience cannot answer the subconscious question in their head

number 1, it's easy to set up, you just test another audience.. but if you test another audience as well, how about bluetick?

Text:
Yg kedua ni sgt penting. kat tiktok ada 1 sifu yg bagus, dia ajar detail kau kena reply apa, apa expected soalan yg customer akan tanya..

but honestly, itu taktik. Strategi yg utama kau kena faham, setiap audience yang whatsapp kau tu, dorg JELAS berminat nak tahu produk kau..
Translated Text:
The second one is very important. at tiktok there is a good sifu, he teaches you the details of what you have to reply, what are the expected questions that the customer will ask..

but honestly, that's a tactic. The main strategy you have to understand is that every audience that whatsapps you, is CLEARLY interested in knowing your product..

Text:
TAPI..

Kalau dorg bluetick lepas kau bagitahu A-Z mungkin dorg tak jelas dgn jawapan yang dorg cari pada soalan ini...

"What is the GOOD REASON for me to buy now?"

Kerat jari, kebanyakkan biz owner sendiri x tahu apa nk jawab kalau betul ada customer yg tanya direct soalan ni
Translated Text:
BUT..

If you bluetick then you tell A-Z, maybe you are not clear with the answer you are looking for to this question...

"What is the GOOD REASON for me to buy now?"

Fingers crossed, most biz owners themselves don't know what to answer if it's true that there are customers who ask this question directly

Text:
Its all about psychology.

Yg biz owner tu meh sini bersila jap dpan aku..

Aku nk pesan, jgn syok sendiri dgn produk kau. Kau boleh cerita kau berenang masuk lautan api utk cari material buat produk kau..

Tapi klu poin tu buat org tak beli, rugi je badan kau berasap.
Translated Text:
Its all about psychology.

The biz owner is almost here standing cross-legged in front of me..

I want to order, don't shock yourself with your product. Can you tell me that you swam into the ocean of fire to find material for your product..

But if that's the point for people who don't buy, it's a loss for your body to smoke.

Text:
Instead, selalu kaji apa masalah audience kau yg dorg rasa tak confident nk beli sekarang..

aku bgi contoh in my case, aku jual mee sanggul..

Dlu aku bagi harga je, bluetick, asal aku bagi harga je bluetick..okay so boleh nmpk dorg bluetick sbb harga..

and then..jeng jeng jeng
Translated Text:
Instead, always study the problems of your audience who don't feel confident to buy now..

I'll give you an example in my case, I sell bun noodles..

I used to give the price, bluetick, originally I gave the price only bluetick..okay so can I show you bluetick for the price..

and then.. jeng jeng jeng

Text:
aku kaji punya kaji, scroll komen2 kat post aku, borak2 sikit dgn customer dan bukan customer..aku akhirnya dpt tahu reason knp dorg bluetick harga aku sbb

dorg tak boleh brain knp mee sanggul aku mahal dari mee kuning biasa

weh auto mudah nk setel bila kita dpt tahu prob ni..
Translated Text:
I have researched, scrolled through the comments on my post, chatted a little with customers and non-customers.. I finally found out the reason why they bluetick my price as follows

I can't think why my bun noodles are more expensive than normal yellow noodles

Well, auto is easy to set when we know this problem..

Text: sblm ni aku join Growth Mastermind oleh Owner Circle, bawah company aku kerja dlu. Masa tu yg ajar kitorg ialah coach kepada Datuk Nicol David, Michel Gagne. Dia marah kitorg sape yg typing. Dia paksa kitorg tulis apa yg dia ajar..especially journal. Ini yg aku boleh share..
Translated Text: Earlier today, I joined Growth Mastermind by Owner Circle, under the company I worked for. At that time the one who taught us was Datuk Nicol David's coach, Michel Gagne. He is angry with the one who is typing. He forced us to write what he taught..especially journal. This is what I can share..

Text:
klu korg blur nk tulis apa dlm journal. Just jawab je soalan ni hari2. sblum tu, soalan2 ni berkenaan growth korang sbnarnya..xkira la utk business, personal, career etc.

so here we go:

1) 3 grateful things today

kau kena fikir apa nikmat yg kau patut syukuri masa tu dan tulis
Translated Text:
I'm not sure what to write in the journal. Just answer this question today. Before that, these questions are really about your growth.. think about it for business, personal, career etc.

so here we go:

1) 3 grateful things today

You have to think about what favors you should be thankful for at that time and write it down

Text:
2) Apa perkara yang saya sudah buat dengan betul?

Utk soalan ni, korang tulis apakah tindakan yg korang dah buat dlm menjawab any challenges or any commitment towards your goal yg korang rasa/yakin betul.
Translated Text:
2) What things have I done correctly?

For this question, write down what actions you have taken in answering any challenges or any commitment towards your goal that you feel/believe is right.

Text:
3) Apakah yg perlu dipertingkatkan lagi dalam usaha ke arah gol saya?

Soalan ni let u sit back and wonder your mind on things that should you improve. maybe something about challenges ur facing today, or your personal or mind issues that need to be improved.
Translated Text:
3) Apakah yg perlu dipertingkatkan lagi dalam usaha ke arah gol saya?

Soalan ni let u sit back and wonder your mind on things that should you improve. maybe something about challenges ur facing today, or your personal or mind issues that need to be improved.

Text:
4) Apakah 20% effort yang perlu saya buat utk capai 80% of the result?

soalan ni let u think and make decision on efficiency action you should take in growing ur bisnes, personal, career etc. You need to think 2 more options of action and see which apply the 80/20 rule
Translated Text:
4) Apakah 20% effort yang perlu saya buat utk capai 80% of the result?

soalan ni let u think and make decision on efficiency action you should take in growing ur bisnes, personal, career etc. You need to think 2 more options of action and see which apply the 80/20 rule

Text:
5) 3 Important Things To Do and 3 Urgent Things To Do

soalan ni biasa dah korang dgr. Just need to write it down XD
Translated Text:
5) 3 Important Things To Do and 3 Urgent Things To Do

soalan ni biasa dah korang dgr. Just need to write it down XD

Text:
Itu je soalannya, hari2 kitorg kena tulis dan hantar kat whatsapp group. kalau tak hantar kena denda bayar RM 200/hari. 

lama2 jadi habit. and it really clear ur mind..other than that..lepas korang jawab semua soalan2 ni, korang boleh je tulis mende lain. 

XD
Translated Text:
That's the question, every day we have to write it and send it to the whatsapp group. if you don't send it, you have to pay a fine of RM 200/day.

It's been a habit for a long time. and it really clear ur mind..other than that..after you answer all these questions, you can write elsewhere.

XD

Text: Cyberjaya dilancarkan pada tahun 1997, dan akan mencapai ulang tahunnya yang ke-25 tahun hadapan. Walaupun ramai yang cakap Cyberjaya ni satu kegagalan, tetapi tidak benar bagi saya. Credit: Cyberview https://t.co/T4mSJIUhPb
Translated Text: Cyberjaya was launched in 1997, and will reach its 25th anniversary next year. Although many people say that Cyberjaya is a failure, it is not true for me. Credit: Cyberview https://t.co/T4mSJIUhPb

Text: Cyberjaya merupakan satu bandar ‘work-in-progress’ dan akan mencapai potensinya dalam masa 10-15 tahun lagi.
Translated Text: Cyberjaya is a 'work-in-progress' city and will reach its potential in the next 10-15 years.

Text: Ini kerana Cyberjaya merupakan special economic zone MSC dan mempunyai kebenaran merancang yang sangat ‘strict’ di bawah @MPSepang dan @CyberviewMY.
Translated Text: This is because Cyberjaya is a MSC special economic zone and has very 'strict' planning permission under @MPSepang and @CyberviewMY.

Text: Mungkin sebab itu Cyberjaya bukan pilihan utama developers. Sebab lain juga mungkin banyak developers tak faham dengan potensi Cyberjaya.
Translated Text: Maybe that's why Cyberjaya is not the main choice of developers. Another reason may be that many developers do not understand the potential of Cyberjaya.

Text: Prima Avenue merupakan antara pembangun persendirian terawal di Cyberjaya dan mereka telah membawa banyak pembangunan dan F&B ke sini seperti Old Town dan @McDMalaysia https://t.co/rXlB0MHhJ5
Translated Text: Prima Avenue is one of the earliest private developers in Cyberjaya and they have brought many developments and F&B here such as Old Town and @McDMalaysia https://t.co/rXlB0MHhJ5

Text: Sebarang pembangunan di Cyberjaya perlu dikelola oleh @CyberviewMY dan @MPSepang berdasarkan kepada pelan induk (masterplan) oleh @kpkt_gov yang diterbitkan pada sekitar tahun 1997.
Translated Text: Any development in Cyberjaya needs to be managed by @CyberviewMY and @MPSepang based on the master plan by @kpkt_gov published around 1997.

Text: Pelan tersebut sangat terperinci; misalnya pembangunan komersil seperti di kawasan Flagship Zone mesti mempunyai jarak minimum 12m dari jalan utama. https://t.co/gNLzKbcIOw
Translated Text: The plan is very detailed; for example, commercial development such as in the Flagship Zone area must have a minimum distance of 12m from the main road. https://t.co/gNLzKbcIOw

Text: dan bangunan seperti hospital hanya boleh dibina dengan ketinggian tertentu sahaja. https://t.co/qpPJ3Frcdy
Translated Text: and buildings such as hospitals can only be built with a certain height. https://t.co/qpPJ3Frcdy

Text: dan bahu jalan mempunyai lebar yang tertentu dan sesuai untuk basikal dan pejalan kaki. Taman-taman besar dan kecil akan sentiasa diutamakan dalam sebarang pembangunan. https://t.co/PCRTppKOjy
Translated Text: and the shoulder of the road has a certain width and is suitable for bicycles and pedestrians. Large and small parks will always be prioritized in any development. https://t.co/PCRTppKOjy

Text: Baru-baru ini, @CyberviewMY memperoleh semula kebenaran membangun kesemua flagship zone Cyberjaya drpd @SetiaHaruman https://t.co/YzYb5U3Mct
Translated Text: Recently, @CyberviewMY regained permission to develop all Cyberjaya flagship zones from @SetiaHaruman https://t.co/YzYb5U3Mct

Text: Pastinya, Cyberjaya, jika dibangunkan secara teliti dan mampan, tidak akan menjadi over crowded dan caca merba seperti KL, Subang, Puchong etc.
Translated Text: Certainly, Cyberjaya, if developed carefully and sustainably, will not become overcrowded and crowded like KL, Subang, Puchong etc.

Text: Dengan kombinasi teknologi dan alam semulajadi, dan terletak berdekatan ibu negara, pastinya tiada lagi Cyberjaya yang lain pada masa akan datang. Melainkan negara kita menjadi kaya seperti dahulu dan mempunyai kadar pembangunan yg pesat seperti zaman 1990an.
Translated Text: With a combination of technology and nature, and located near the nation's capital, there will surely be no other Cyberjaya in the future. Unless our country becomes rich like before and has a rapid development rate like in the 1990s.

Text: Pembangunan di sekitar Cyberjaya seperti Dengkil, Salak Tinggi & sbgnya akan menggalakkan lagi pertumbuhan Cyberjaya. https://t.co/VyWAi18sTt
Translated Text: Development around Cyberjaya such as Dengkil, Salak Tinggi & as it will further encourage the growth of Cyberjaya. https://t.co/VyWAi18sTt

Text: Sekian perkongsian saya. Follow me for more updates in tech, innovation and the city that I love since 1997, Cyberjaya.
Translated Text: That's all I have to share. Follow me for more updates in tech, innovation and the city that I love since 1997, Cyberjaya.

Text: Pertama sekali, Tweet ini bukan nak promote Cyberjaya, tapi untuk memberi pandangan mengapa saya ‘gila’ dengan tempat ini
Translated Text: First of all, this Tweet is not to promote Cyberjaya, but to give an insight into why I am 'crazy' about this place

Text: Saya mula berminat dengan Cyberjaya pada tahun 1998. Saya ternampak iklan di dalam surat khabar mengenai Cyberjaya. Pada masa itu sayu baru dalam tahun pertama di universiti. Cyberjaya dilancarkan pada tahun 1997 setahun selepas penubuhan Multimedia Super Corrdor (MSC)
Translated Text: I became interested in Cyberjaya in 1998. I saw an advertisement in the newspaper about Cyberjaya. At that time the new melancholy was in the first year at university. Cyberjaya was launched in 1997 a year after the establishment of the Multimedia Super Corridor (MSC)

Text: Inilah iklan tersebut. Cyberjaya — di mana semua infrastruktur dapat dipantau secara jarak jauh. Konsep Internet-of-Things (IoT) sudah wujud pada masa itu oleh Cyberjaya. Photo Credit: @Rasbima https://t.co/fHX0d5B4W5
Translated Text: Here is the ad. Cyberjaya — where all infrastructure can be monitored remotely. The concept of Internet-of-Things (IoT) already existed at that time by Cyberjaya. Photo Credit: @Rasbima https://t.co/fHX0d5B4W5

Text: Saya sangat teruja dengan iklan ini dan membuat keputusan untuk bekerja dan menetap di Cyberjaya pada suatu hari nanti.
Translated Text: I was very excited by this advertisement and decided to work and live in Cyberjaya one day.

Text: Namun selepas keluar dari universiti, saya tidak terus bekerja di Cyberjaya. Saya memperluaskan pengalaman bekerja saya di negeri orang.
Translated Text: However, after leaving university, I did not continue to work in Cyberjaya. I am expanding my working experience in the land of people.

Text: Pada tahun 2013, saya kembali ke tanah air dan mula mencari kerja di sekitar Cyberjaya. Pada suatu hari, saya ternampak iklan di FB mengenai MaGIC @mymagic_my. Saya mengikuti perkembangan agensi ini dan mencuba nasib saya.
Translated Text: In 2013, I returned to my homeland and started looking for work around Cyberjaya. One day, I saw an ad on FB about MaGIC @mymagic_my. I followed the development of this agency and tried my luck.

Text: Pada awal tahun 2015, saya mendapat kerja di MaGIC untuk menjalankan program keusahawanan. Agensi ini menjadi sangat popular dalam masa yang singkat dan menjadi tumpuan kerajaan dari luar negara. https://t.co/xovxbiu4Au
Translated Text: In early 2015, I got a job at MaGIC to run the entrepreneurship program. This agency became very popular in a short time and became the focus of governments from abroad. https://t.co/xovxbiu4Au

Text: Sebelum itu, saya mendapat tahu bahawa Cyberview @CyberviewMY merupakan syarikat @MOFmalaysia yang bertanggungjawab untuk membangunkan Cyberjaya. Pada tahun 2017, saya mendapat tawaran untuk bekerja di Cyberview.
Translated Text: Before that, I found out that Cyberview @CyberviewMY is the @MOFmalaysia company responsible for developing Cyberjaya. In 2017, I got an offer to work at Cyberview.

Text: Saya bertanggungjawab untuk menjalankan program inovasi untuk Cyberjaya. Di sinilah saya berpeluang untuk memberi sumbangan sepenuhnya kepada pembangunan Cyberjaya. https://t.co/EOVWaFrghw
Translated Text: I am responsible for running the innovation program for Cyberjaya. This is where I have the opportunity to contribute fully to the development of Cyberjaya. https://t.co/EOVWaFrghw

Text: Oleh kerana peranan ekosistem sangat penting, saya bersama rakan sekerja saya banyak membawa masuk projek perintis (pilot projects) yang kebanyakannya tidak melibatkan sebarang kos.
Translated Text: Because the role of the ecosystem is very important, my colleagues and I bring in a lot of pilot projects, most of which do not involve any cost.

Text: Di antaranya adalah bike-sharing, cashless society, vehicle counting sensors. https://t.co/FPzLwpYc6N
Translated Text: Among them are bike-sharing, cashless society, vehicle counting sensors. https://t.co/FPzLwpYc6N

Text: Kami juga memperkenalkan autonomous store, e-scooter Tryke yang banyak di tepi tasik sekarang, dan Cyberjaya Farmers Market. https://t.co/1FcaH0ToVM
Translated Text: We also introduced autonomous stores, Tryke e-scooters, which are now widely available on the banks of the lake, and the Cyberjaya Farmers Market. https://t.co/1FcaH0ToVM

Text: Kami berjaya masuk syarikat dron @poladrone dan syarikat Robotics Delivery HelloWorld Robotics. Ini semua syarikat tempatan, dan juga urban-farming. https://t.co/0gTeViE0R9
Translated Text: We successfully entered drone company @poladrone and Robotics Delivery company HelloWorld Robotics. These are all local companies, and also urban-farming. https://t.co/0gTeViE0R9

Text: Saya nak buat test sendiri sebab petang tadi dapat notification dalam MySejahtera yang saya ni casual contact 😣 no idea from where. Memang skrg xde symptoms pun. https://t.co/UnkLierD8e
Translated Text: I want to do the test myself because last evening I got a notification in MySejahtera that I am a casual contact 😣 no idea from where. There are no symptoms now. https://t.co/UnkLierD8e

Text: Thankfully our company @Aerodyne_Group sponsored this test kit drpd @MyMEDKAD. Jadi malam tadi lepas balik dari kerja terus buat test sendiri. Memang mudah.
Translated Text: Thankfully our company @Aerodyne_Group sponsored this test kit from @MyMEDKAD. So last night I got back from work and did the test myself. It's easy.

Text: Sebelum mula, basuh tangan sebersih-bersihnya untuk mengelakkan pencemaran kepada test kit. Buat dekat tempat yang terang.
Translated Text: Before starting, wash your hands thoroughly to avoid contaminating the test kit. Make it near a bright place.

Text: 1/ Keluarkan tiub buffer ekstraksi ni dan letak atas belakang kotak sebagai ‘holder’. https://t.co/iWfRR6cbXD
Translated Text: 1/ Remove the extraction buffer tube and place it on the back of the box as a 'holder'. https://t.co/iWfRR6cbXD

Text: 2/ Dalam test kit ni ada dua swab — satu untuk mengambil sample calitan air liur, yg satu lagi dari hidung. https://t.co/51KWQvezzd
Translated Text: 2/ In this test kit there are two swabs - one to take a saliva smear sample, the other from the nose. https://t.co/51KWQvezzd

Text: 3/ Ambil sample mengikut arahan yg diberikan. Jgn risau, user manual yg disertakan sangat jelas. Swab pertama untuk air liur. https://t.co/soLdrMOMNJ
Translated Text: 3/ Take a sample according to the instructions given. Don't worry, the included user manual is very clear. First swab for saliva. https://t.co/soLdrMOMNJ

Text: 4/ Masukkan swab pertama ke dalam tiub dan gunakan swab kedua untuk mengambil sample daripada bahagian dalam hidung. https://t.co/Zxzz1yFOrq
Translated Text: 4/ Insert the first swab into the tube and use the second swab to take a sample from the inside of the nose. https://t.co/Zxzz1yFOrq

Text: 5/ Masukkan kedua-dua swab ke dalam tiub, rendamkan dan goncang. Arahan dan ilustrasi jelas dan mudah untuk difahami. https://t.co/AbB8Zt3cbP
Translated Text: 5/ Insert both swabs into the tube, soak and shake. The instructions and illustrations are clear and easy to understand. https://t.co/AbB8Zt3cbP

Text: 6/ Langkah yang berikutnya membuatkan saya nervous 😅 sample dah ready so kita akan test skrg. Buka tiub tersebut dan letak dua titis ke alat ujian tersebut. https://t.co/QGAVqixLfX
Translated Text: 6/ The next step makes me nervous 😅 the sample is ready so we will test it now. Open the tube and put two drops into the test device. https://t.co/QGAVqixLfX

Text: 7/ Skrg kita tunggu. Sebenarnya dalam beberapa minit saja result dah keluar. Syukur my result negative. Kalau positive akan ada dua garisan pada C & T. https://t.co/c4OdoiRy0c
Translated Text: 7/ Now we wait. Actually, in just a few minutes, the result is out. Thank goodness my result was negative. If positive there will be two lines on C & T. https://t.co/c4OdoiRy0c

Text: 8/ Ini contoh ujian yg ditunjukkan dalam user manual. https://t.co/YVDVvRkmjV
Translated Text: 8/ This is an example of the test shown in the user manual. https://t.co/YVDVvRkmjV

Text: 9/ OK dah.. result dah dapat x risau sangat skrg. Last step, update dekat MySejahtera > COVID-19 Self Test > Update Self Test Result. Ikut arahan dalam skrin dan submit. https://t.co/nsbQi8do04
Translated Text: 9/ OK, the results have been obtained, I'm not really worried now. Last step, update near MySejahtera > COVID-19 Self Test > Update Self Test Result. Follow the instructions on the screen and submit. https://t.co/nsbQi8do04

Text: 10/ Itulah perkongsian saya buat self test Covid-19 dekat rumah. For info, harga test kit ni RM39.90 di pasaran. Harap2 harga akan turun sbb memang kira mahal jugak. 😅 take care everyone!
Translated Text: 10/ That's my sharing for self-testing Covid-19 near home. For info, the price of this test kit is RM39.90 in the market. Hope the price will go down because it is expensive. 😅 take care everyone!

Text: Saya membesar dalam era 90an di mana ekonomi Malaysia membangun paling pesat pada masa itu. Purata penumbuhan GDP Malaysia pada masa itu adalah 9.48%. Memang banyak negara jealous dengan kita. https://t.co/vqLdfpCfWh

Text: Sebab itulah pada awal 90-an, PM ke-4 Malaysia Tun Dr @chedetofficial sudah mula membuat rancangan jangka panjang untuk membuatkan Malaysia negara membangun. Hampir tiap2 hari dengar lagu Wawasan 2020. 😅
Translated Text: That's why in the early 90s, Malaysia's 4th PM Tun Dr @chedetofficial started making long-term plans to make Malaysia a developing country. Listen to the song Wawasan 2020 almost every day. 😅

Text: Pada masa yang sama, kerajaan juga mula melabur dalam projek mega seperti Putrajaya (1995), Petronas Twin Towers (1992) & KLIA (1993). Some people said membazir but they were future investments for the country. https://t.co/X7G8HeQbmq
Translated Text: At the same time, the government also started investing in mega projects such as Putrajaya (1995), Petronas Twin Towers (1992) & KLIA (1993). Some people said it was a waste but they were future investments for the country. https://t.co/X7G8HeQbmq

Text: Cyberjaya was the final piece of all the mega projects when it was launched in 17th May, 1997. Ia merupakan nukleus kepada Multimedia Super Corridor (MSC) = KLCC + Putrajaya + Cyberjaya + KLIA.
Translated Text: Cyberjaya was the final piece of all the mega projects when it was launched in 17th May, 1997. It is the nucleus for the Multimedia Super Corridor (MSC) = KLCC + Putrajaya + Cyberjaya + KLIA.

Text: Secara amnya, Koridor Raya Multimedia bukan sahaja untuk  menarik syarikat IT antarabangsa, tetapi juga tempat di mana teknologi baru dapat dibangunkan untuk mewujudkan ‘multiplier effect’ dalam ekonomi Malaysia.
Translated Text: In general, the Multimedia Corridor is not only to attract international IT companies, but also a place where new technologies can be developed to create a 'multiplier effect' in the Malaysian economy.

Text: MSC menjadi sangat popular di dalam dunia IT tempatan dan antarabangsa. Orang-orang kenamaan IT seperti Bill Gates pernah menjadi penasihat kepada MSC dan melawat Cyberjaya sebanyak dua kali. https://t.co/aO0CmAJiWf
Translated Text: MSC is becoming very popular in the local and international IT world. IT luminaries such as Bill Gates have been advisors to MSC and visited Cyberjaya twice. https://t.co/aO0CmAJiWf

Text: MSC pun dah masuk kamus Cambridge sekarang. 😁 https://t.co/neVui12RtV
Translated Text: MSC has entered the Cambridge dictionary now. 😁 https://t.co/neVui12RtV

Text: Semasa pelancaran Cyberjaya pada tahun 1997, upacara tersebut tidak semeriah seperti pelancaran Putrajaya kerana Malaysia mengalami krisis kewangan pada masa itu. Credit: Cyberview / NST. https://t.co/D8uM4opJFZ
Translated Text: During the launch of Cyberjaya in 1997, the ceremony was not as lively as the launch of Putrajaya because Malaysia was experiencing a financial crisis at that time. Credit: Cyberview / NST. https://t.co/D8uM4opJFZ

Text: Tetapi pada masa itu, konsep MSC memang susah nak difahami. Kini, konsep-konsep seperti ride sharing (Grab), e-Commerce (Lazada/Shopee) etc. merupakan contoh teknologi yang nak dizahirkan. Jack Ma (pengasas Alibaba) mendapat inspirasi drpd MSC. https://t.co/XF4CcaApu5
Translated Text: But at that time, the concept of MSC was difficult to understand. Now, concepts such as ride sharing (Grab), e-Commerce (Lazada/Shopee) etc. is an example of technology that wants to be expressed. Jack Ma (founder of Alibaba) was inspired by MSC. https://t.co/XF4CcaApu5

Text: Ramai orang tanya, apasal banyak perumahan? For a city to thrive, you need critical mass / big enough population. Cyberjaya dapat menampung sehingga 240,000 orang, mungkin lebih sedikit daripada itu pada masa hadapan.
Translated Text: Many people ask, why is there so much housing? For a city to thrive, you need critical mass / big enough population. Cyberjaya can accommodate up to 240,000 people, maybe even less in the future.

Translated Text: In the past, people didn't want to live in Cyberjaya because there weren't many housing options. Again, the MEX highway had not been built when Cyberjaya was launched in 1999.

Text: Ini menyebabkan orang rasa Cyberjaya ni jauh. Persepsi ini masih wujud sampai skrg walaupun skrg dari KL ke Cyberjaya hanya 25-30 minit.
Translated Text: This causes people to think that Cyberjaya is far away. This perception still exists even now even though it is only 25-30 minutes from KL to Cyberjaya.

Text: Konsep Multimedia Super Corridor atau MSC bukan tertumpu kepada Cyberjaya sahaja. Kawasan MSC bermula dari KLCC sehinggalah ke KLIA. Cyberjaya merupakan ‘nukleus’ kepada MSC.
Translated Text: The Multimedia Super Corridor or MSC concept is not only focused on Cyberjaya. The MSC area starts from KLCC all the way to KLIA. Cyberjaya is the 'nucleus' of MSC.

Text: Jadi, x salah jika ada syarikat-syarikat lain nak beroperasi di tempat lain selain daripada Cyberjaya.
Translated Text: So, it is not wrong if there are other companies that want to operate in places other than Cyberjaya.

Text: Cyberjaya ni bukan pembangunan jangka pendek jadi tak dinafikan bahawa masih ada lagi yg perlu diperbaiki, contohnya direct bus service ke KLIA/KL, Puchong, PJ & Seremban etc.
Translated Text: Cyberjaya is not a short-term development so there is no denying that there are still things that need to be improved, for example direct bus service to KLIA/KL, Puchong, PJ & Seremban etc.

Text: IBM, T-Systems & HSBC dah nak keluar dari Cyberjaya. Ya betul. Syarikat gergasi macam begini memang akan selalu membuat evaluation tentang kos operasi. Kalau insentif kerajaan dah tamat memang akan ada risiko keluar dr Cyberjaya, tetapi...
Translated Text: IBM, T-Systems & HSBC wants to leave Cyberjaya. That is correct. Giant companies like this will always make an evaluation about operating costs. If the government's incentives are over, there will indeed be a risk of leaving Cyberjaya, but...

Text: Banyak syarikat permulaan (startup) & SMEs mula bertapak di Cyberjaya e.g @Aerodyne_Group, world’s #2 drone service provider. Deriv baru shj beli bangunan Quill sebelah IBM untuk dijadikan global HQ. @hematogenix syarikat pengkajian barah dari USA baru beroperasi di sini.
Translated Text: Many startup companies & SMEs are starting to establish a foothold in Cyberjaya e.g. @Aerodyne_Group, world's #2 drone service provider. The new Deriv just bought the Quill building next to IBM to be used as a global HQ. @hematogenix a cancer research company from the USA has just started operating here.

Text: Syarikat animasi tempatan @MonstaOfficial_ penerbit @BoBoiBoy beroperasi di sini, begitu juga Digital Durian penerbit Didi & Friends, syarikat R&D DreamEdge etc.
Translated Text: Local animation company @MonstaOfficial_ producer @BoBoiBoy operates here, as does Digital Durian producer Didi & Friends, R&D company DreamEdge etc.

Text: Syarikat telekomunikasi @GlobalNTT dari Jepun yg merupakan syarikat asing mendapat status MSC, baru sahaja membuka data centre ke-5 di Cyberjaya, dan akan berkembang lebih pesat.
Translated Text: The telecommunications company @GlobalNTT from Japan, which is a foreign company with MSC status, has just opened its 5th data center in Cyberjaya, and will grow even more rapidly.

Text: Bayangkan kalau Malaysia xde MSC, Cyberjaya dan @mymdec. Memang x wujud/banyak syarikat2 tempatan yg berjaya seperti hari ini. Rakyat Malaysia sepatutnya berbangga dengan Cyberjaya sepertimana dgn KLCC/Twin Towers.
Translated Text: Imagine if Malaysia had MSC, Cyberjaya and @mymdec. Indeed, there are not many successful local companies like today. Malaysians should be as proud of Cyberjaya as they are of KLCC/Twin Towers.

Text: Memang senang nak kutuk kalau benda2 kita x nampak. So siapa2 yg nak tahu pasal Cyberjaya secara lebih mendalam, boleh lah follow & DM saya. Sekian.
Translated Text: It's easy to curse when we can't see things. So anyone who wants to know more about Cyberjaya, can follow & DM me. So much.

Text:
North Star Metric (NSM) ni @ikaysf pernah mention dekat aku dulu. Dan hari ni aku terdetik nak share.

Basically, North Star Metric ni adalah satu ukuran yang boleh predict long-term success rate sesebuah bisnes. 

Untuk tahu metric ini, korang buat mesti buat 3 perkara ni:
Translated Text:
North Star Metric (NSM) this @ikaysf mentioned to me before. And today I was tickled to share.

Basically, this North Star Metric is a measure that can predict the long-term success rate of a business.

To know this metric, you must do these 3 things:

Text:
1. Revenue
2. Customer Value
3. Progress

Jika dapat mencapai 3 metrics di atas, bisnes akan berkembang secara konsisten.

Sedikit sebanyak tentang North Star Metric ni.

Terms ni Growth Hacker yang selalu guna tapi jarang diguna pakai.

Nak tengok contoh? Sambung thread di bawah
Translated Text:
1. Revenue
2. Customer Values
3. Progress

If you can achieve the 3 metrics above, your business will grow consistently.

A little bit about this North Star Metric.

These terms are Growth Hackers who are always used but rarely used.

Want to see an example? Connect thread below

Text:
E-commerce
- Berapa ramai pelanggan selesaikan order pertama mereka
- Daily purchase Value
- Customer lifetime value (CLV)

Selain itu, aku guna contoh apps yang korang selalu guna.

Facebook = Monthly active users
Airbnb = Number of nights booked
Spotify = Time spent listening
Translated Text:
E-commerce
- How many customers completed their first order
- Daily purchase value
- Customer lifetime value (CLV)

Besides that, I'm using an example of an app that you always use.

Facebook = Monthly active users
Airbnb = Number of nights booked
Spotify = Time spent listening

Text:
Bagaimana nak identify bisnes korang punya North Star Metric?

Tanya soalan ini...

- Apakah yang penting untuk bisnes korang berfungsi?
- Apakah KPI dan metric yang perlu diukur?

North Star Metrics ni perlu masa untuk dibina. Bukan buat sehari terus dapat.
Translated Text:
How to identify your business has North Star Metric?

Ask this question...

- What is important for your business to work?
- What are the KPIs and metrics that need to be measured?

North Star Metrics needs time to build. Not for a day and get it.

Text:
North Star metrics boleh menjadi strategi yang berkesan untuk mencapai sesuatu matlamat.

Itu sahaja perkongsian simple aku pada malam ini.

Harap sedikit sebanyak dapat membantu korang.
Translated Text:
North Star metrics can be an effective strategy to achieve a goal.

That's all my simple sharing tonight.

Hope to be able to help you a little.

Text:
Sales tak datang bergolek.

Menjadi peniaga ni bukan sahaja kena tahu marketing, tapi menjual.

Memang kena belajar bagaimana nak menjual ni. 

Ada yang kalah dekat sini.

Jadi, aku nak rungkaikan sikit point penting dalam buku ini untuk korang faham lagi pasal menjual.
Translated Text:
Sales don't come rolling.

To be a trader you not only have to know marketing, but also to sell.

You really have to learn how to sell this.

There is a loser near here.

So, I want to break down a few important points in this book for you to understand more about selling.

Text:
KENA ADA KPI

Dekat sini penting untuk seorang peniaga set KPI.

Kena tulis berapa yang korang nak achieve dalam masa setahun.

Kalau tidak, korang tiada hala tuju dan plan untuk dicapai.

Bila dah set KPI, baru la korang senang nak set hala tuju untuk achieve goals korang. https://t.co/dSEdqOHnR9
Translated Text:
MUST HAVE KPI

Here it is important for a trader to set KPIs.

Have to write how much you want to achieve in a year.

Otherwise, you have no direction and plan to achieve.

Once you have set the KPI, it is easy to set the direction to achieve your goals. https://t.co/dSEdqOHnR9

Text:
TAHU KENAPA PELANGGAN MEMBELI

Ramai peniaga yang mungkin tidak tahu apa yang sebenarnya prospek nak.

Benda ni antara yang penting bagi aku.

Bila korang menjual, jangan fikir pasal produk kita.

Fikir apa “features & benefit” seseorang itu bakal dapat. https://t.co/sgnsfhAeVA
Translated Text:
KNOW WHY CUSTOMERS BUY

Many traders may not know what the prospect actually is.

This is one of the most important things for me.

When you sell, don't think about our products.

Think what "features & benefit" a person will get. https://t.co/sgnsfhAeVA

Text:
JADI PENDENGAR YANG BAIK

Manusia ni suka bila kita mendengar.

Kawan baik korang mesti nak korang dengar masalah dorang kan?

Sama juga dalam konsep menjual.

Kita dengar dulu baru kita bagi jalan penyelesaian.

Ini adalah strategi menjual yang sangat effective! https://t.co/oJwqmGJXPS
Translated Text:
BE A GOOD LISTENER

Humans like it when we listen.

Your best friend must want you to listen to your problems, right?

Same in the concept of selling.

We listen first before we give a solution.

This is a very effective selling strategy! https://t.co/oJwqmGJXPS

Text:
SENTIASA CERIA & POSITIF

Perasan tak kadang2 ada orang ikut mood bila nak layan pelanggan?

Bila mood baik, layanan baik.
Bila mood tak baik, habis semua kena.

Apa yg aku belajar, semua masalah kita kena tinggal luar pintu.

Bila dengan prospek, kena sentiasa positif dan senyum
Translated Text:
ALWAYS CHEERFUL & POSITIVE

Have you noticed that sometimes there are people who follow the mood when they want to serve customers?

When the mood is good, the service is good.
When the mood is not good, everything ends.

What I learned, all our problems have to stay outside the door.

When dealing with prospects, always be positive and smile

Text:
1. Fahami "Product Margin"

Ramai yang masih lagi tak tahu pengiraan kos bisnes dan boleh menyebabkan kerugian.

Korang kena kira margin korang betul-betul.

*Korang kena kira breakeven cost, barulah tahu pulangan sales dari ads (ROAS) berbaloi atau tidak.
Translated Text:
1. Understand "Product Margin"

Many still don't know how to calculate business costs and can cause losses.

You have to calculate your margin properly.

*You have to calculate the breakeven cost, then you will know if the sales return from ads (ROAS) is worth it or not.

Text:
2. Funnel Website

Check semula funnel website korang.

Penggunaan gambar, copywriting di website mempengaruhi website conversion di website.

Pastikan juga tak lupa install pixel di website untuk fungsi retargetting ads di masa akan datang.
Translated Text:
2. Funnel Websites

Re-check your website funnel.

The use of images, copywriting on the website affects website conversions on the website.

Also make sure you don't forget to install the pixel on the website for the function of retargeting ads in the future.

Text:
3. Website Checkout Flow

Checkout anda di website amatlah penting!

Buat checkout yg mudah. Mudahkan proses pembelian mereka di website.

Jangan biarkan flow pembelian yg terlalu panjang. 

*Elakkan letak form yang terlalu panjang
*Elakkan guna signup bila mereka nak checkout
Translated Text:
3. Website Checkout Flow

Your checkout on the website is very important!

Make an easy checkout. Simplify their purchase process on the website.

Don't let the purchase flow be too long.

*Avoid putting a form that is too long
*Avoid using signup when they want to checkout

Text:
4. Jaga Speed Website

Kalau website korang loading terlalu lama, nanti minat membeli mereka hilang sebab loading sahaja.

Korang yang masih baru nak setup website e-commerce, kena jaga speed website korang.

Nak tahu website laju atau tidak, boleh ke https://t.co/zBT2sgHkbF
Translated Text:
4. Maintain Website Speed

If your website takes too long to load, they will lose interest in buying because of loading.

Those of you who are new to setting up an e-commerce website, have to take care of your website speed.

If you want to know if the website is fast or not, you can go to https://t.co/zBT2sgHkbF

Text:
Ramai yang pelik, dah buat macam-macam iklan tapi still tak berjaya. 

Kalau korang baca thread ni sampai habis, saya nak  kongsikan tips yang wajib korang kuasai untuk buat iklan yang lebih berkesan. 

Selain itu, korang boleh buat pelanggan korang rasa tertarik untuk membeli!🧐
Translated Text:
A lot of people are strange, they have made all kinds of advertisements but still no success.

If you read this thread until the end, I want to share tips that you must master to make more effective ads.

In addition, you can make your customers feel interested in buying!🧐

Text:
1. Market: Kepada siapa kita nak jual (audience)

Tanya soalan ini, "Siapakah audience aku?". Yang ini adalah kepastian yang korang tidak target orang yang bukan target market korang.

Lokasi:
Umur:
Jantina:
Minat/Tingkah laku:

Di atas ini adalah basic dalam mengenali audience.
Translated Text:
1. Market: To whom do we want to sell (audience)

Ask this question, "Who is my audience?". This one is a certainty that you do not target people who are not your target market.

Location:
Age:
Gender:
Interests/Behavior:

The above is basic in knowing the audience.

Text:
2. Message: Copywriting ayat-ayat iklan anda
Tanya soalan ini pula, "Adakah mesej aku akan sampai kepada audience aku?".

Korang tak boleh kenal audience tanpa berborak dgn mereka.

Di sinilah copywriting korang menjadi senjata utama.

Pastikan mereka faham apa yang anda offer.
Translated Text:
2. Message: Copywriting your ad sentences
Ask this question, "Will my message reach my audience?".

You can't know your audience without chatting with them.

This is where your copywriting becomes your main weapon.

Make sure they understand what you offer.

Text:
3. Media: Gambar/Video dalam posting iklan anda
Tanya soalan ini juga, "Macam mana aku nak tarik perhatian audience dengan cepat?"

Creative menjadi sebab kenapa audience akan tertarik dengan bisnes korang.

Fokus  membina creative yang dapat menarik perhatian dan interactive.
Translated Text:
3. Media: Pictures/Videos in your ad posting
Ask this question as well, "How do I get the audience's attention quickly?"

Creative is the reason why the audience will be interested in your business.

Focus on creating creative that can attract attention and be interactive.

Text:
Tips 1 : Copywriting Yang "Personalized"

Elakkan buat copywriting yang terlalu "general".

Lebih ramai pelanggan akan tertarik untuk interact dengan iklan korang jika copywriting lebih "specific" dan "personalized".
Translated Text:
Tip 1: "Personalized" Copywriting

Avoid doing copywriting that is too "general".

More customers will be interested to interact with your advertisement if the copywriting is more "specific" and "personalized".

Text:
Tips 2: Pecahkan Target Audience

Korang akan dapat tarik lebih ramai pelanggan jika korang dapat kenal pasti siapa pelanggan ‘sebenar’ korang.

Kalau korang nak jual skincare mungkin boleh pecah–pecah kan iklan ikut niche target audience anda.

Jangan buat terlalu "general".
Translated Text:
Tip 2: Break down the Target Audience

You will be able to attract more customers if you can identify who your 'real' customers are.

If you want to sell skincare, you may be able to split the ads according to your niche target audience.

Don't make it too "general".

Text:
Tips 3: Tunjuk Pencapaian

Apa yang telah dicapai oleh produk/servis korang?

Ada tak apa-apa kejayaan yang produk anda dah capai?

Korang boleh share dalam copywriting/creative korang & akan jadi lebih berpengaruh.

Cth: "5,214 sudah mendapat results dalam masa 3 bulan"
Translated Text:
Tip 3: Show Achievements

What has your product/service achieved?

Is there any success that your product has achieved?

You can share in your copywriting/creative & will be more influential.

Eg: "5,214 already got results in 3 months"

Text:
Tips 4: Authority

Ini adalah cara yang dapat menguatkan kepercayaan prospek kepada produk korang.

Ada tak pakar yang iktiraf produk anda?

Ada dapat sijil ke?

Kalau ada, korang boleh masukkan dalam copywriting/creative.

Kalau tak ada, jangan la korang pandai-pandai reka.
Translated Text:
Tip 4: Authority

This is a way that can strengthen the prospect's trust in your product.

Are there any experts who recognize your product?

Did you get a certificate?

If there is, you can enter it in copywriting/creative.

If you don't have it, don't be smart about it.

Snap - Attention Grabbing
Benefits - Core Benefits
Actions - Call-To-Actions

6. Semak Semula Funnel Anda

Snap - Attention Grabbing
Benefits - Core Benefits
Actions - Call-To-Actions

Text:
7. Split Testing Everything
Ramai ingat testing ini hanya dibuat kepada creative sahaja. Fokus juga testing ad set & campaign. Ini untuk mendapatkan "Winning Campaign, Ad Set & Ads"

8. Retargeting
Retargeting ni ibarat reminder kepada audience anda. Lebih mudah untuk convert.
Translated Text:
7. Split Testing Everything
Many remember that this test is only made for creatives. Also focus on testing ad sets & campaigns. This is to get "Winning Campaign, Ad Set & Ads"

8. Retargeting
Retargeting is like a reminder to your audience. It's easier to convert.

Text:
9. Install Pixel
Jgn lupa install Pixel di website. Pixel ini bantu korang track interaction di website. Ini akan bantu retargeting & lookalike audience.

10. Upsell/Cross-Sell
Setiap "Purchase" yang anda dapat, anda boleh buat iklan untuk upsell/cross-sell produk anda yang lain.
Translated Text:
9. Install Pixels
Don't forget to install Pixel on the website. These pixels help you track interaction on the website. This will help retargeting & lookalike audience.

10. Upsell/Cross-Sell
Every "Purchase" you get, you can create an advertisement to upsell/cross-sell your other products.

Text:
Apa cuba aku sampaikan adalah "value".

Mungkin value kita tidak dihargai oleh certain company, tapi dengan "value" yang kau ada tu boleh dibawa ke company lain.

Your value doesn't equal to company culture.

Value stays with you sampai bila-bila. Jadi, fokus tingkatkan value.
Translated Text:
What I'm trying to convey is "value".

Maybe certain companies don't value our values, but with the "values" you have, you can bring them to other companies.

Your values ​​don't equal to company culture.

Value stays with you until whenever. So, focus on increasing value.

Text:

There are people working to build career growth, learn new skills, build networking and etc.

Text:

Dorang masih lagi productive tanpa kerja lebih masa
Translated Text:
Working hard doesn't necessarily mean overtime.

I also applied it in my company, only focusing on 9-5.

More than 5pm, that's your right if you want to live your life or want to work overtime. Same on Sundays.

You are still productive without overtime

Text:
1. Pastikan produk ada demand

Buat research & sentiasa pastikan jual produk yang ada permintaan tinggi.

80% daripada masa anda sepatutnya habis untuk mencari produk yang betul & ada permintaan.

80% of your time should be spent finding the right product & there is a request.

Text:
2. Kenalpasti bakal pelanggan

Audience research adalah perkara yang penting selepas buat research tentang produk.

Kenalpasti bakal pelanggan anda dengan menggunakan "customer persona".
Translated Text:
2. Identify potential customers

Audience research is an important thing after doing research about the product.

Identify your potential customers by using "customer persona".

Text:
3. Sediakan copywriting & creative iklan yang menarik

Selepas dah buat research, sediakan copywriting & creative yang menarik.

Ini adalah senjata utama dalam buat iklan. Fokus dalam pembuatan content yang bukan sahaja berkualiti, tetapi converting.
Translated Text:
3. Prepare copywriting & Interesting ad creative

After doing research, prepare copywriting & Interesting creative.

This is the main weapon in advertising. Focus on creating content that is not only quality, but converting.

Text:
4. Testing! (Dengan budget yang rendah)

Pastikan anda buat testing.

- Testing audience
- Testing copywriting & creative

2 di atas ini adalah antara yang penting bila nak buat testing.

Lepas dah confident dan dapat results, slowly boleh naikkan budget.
Translated Text:
4. Testing! (With a low budget)

Make sure you do testing.

- Audience testing
- Testing copywriting & creative

Once you are confident and get results, you can slowly increase the budget.

Text:
Dalam storytelling, kita kongsi apa kita rasa. Bukan untuk menjual.

1. Storytelling ni untuk tarik perhatian

2. Storytelling juga lebih mudah diingati

3. Prospek boleh “terbeli” produk korang.

Jadi, storytelling bukan fokus menjual. Lebih kepada kongsi apa kita tahu.
Translated Text:
In storytelling, we share what we feel. Not to sell.

1. Storytelling is to attract attention

2. Storytelling is also easier to remember

3. Prospects can "buy" your product.

So, storytelling is not the focus of selling. Rather than sharing what we know.

Text:
Konsep storytelling ni bagi orang sambung the conversation & minta pendapat orang lain.

Pembaca akan lebih seronok dengan cerita lebih dari posting biasa.

Biasanya, bila ada storytelling yang baik akan mendapatkan perhatian orang untuk tahu anda lebih mendalam.
Translated Text:
This storytelling concept is for people to connect the conversation & ask other people's opinion.

Readers will have more fun with stories than regular posts.

Usually, if there is good storytelling, it will get people's attention to know you more deeply.

Text:
Ini semua penting bila nak berniaga.

Buat orang kenal kita sebanyak & sedalam mungkin.

Konsep storytelling tidak tertakluk hanya pada kisah hidup kita.

Tetapi anda juga boleh gunakan isu terkini dan kongsi pendapat anda, kemudian boleh relatekan dengan bisnes anda.
Translated Text:
This is all important when doing business.

Make people know us as much & as deep as possible.

The concept of storytelling is not only subject to the story of our lives.

But you can also use the latest issues and share your opinion, then you can relate to your business.

Text:
Teknik storytelling yang berkesan? Korang boleh tengok formula di bawah.

1. Headline
2. Body text 1
3. Body text 2
4. Solution
5. Call to Action (CTA)

Suggestions aku, fokus lebih banyak masa dalam HEADLINE. 

Sebab bila kita dah mula bercerita, senang nak teruskan menulis.
Translated Text:
Effective storytelling techniques? You can see the formula below.

1. Headlines
2. Body text 1
3. Body text 2
4. Solution
5. Call to Action (CTA)

My suggestions, focus more time on the HEADLINE.

Because when we start telling stories, it's easy to continue writing.

Text:
HEADLINE SUGGESTIONS

1. Bagi soalan - “Bagaimana saya boleh dapat jualan 6 angka dalam masa 30 hari.

2. Gunakan nombor - “3 tips mudah untuk buat marketing yang menjana sales 6 angka!”

3. Gunakan “Jangan” - “Jangan baca kalau anda takde niat nak kembangkan bisnes!”
Translated Text:
HEADLINE SUGGESTIONS

1. For the question - “How can I get 6 figure sales in 30 days.

2. Use numbers - "3 easy tips to create marketing that generates 6-figure sales!"

3. Use "Don't" - "Don't read if you don't intend to grow your business!"

Text:
4. Share “Rahsia” anda - “Rahsia mendapatkan sales secara konsisten”

5. Babitkan orang yang ada influence - “Kenapa (insert public figure name) boleh mula semula lepas rugi RMX,XXX,XXX”

6. Gunakan konsep “harapan” - “Boleh ke aku capai RM1,000,000 pertama aku tahun ini?”
Translated Text:
4. Share your "Secret" - "The secret to getting consistent sales"

5. Involve people with influence - "Why can (insert public figure name) start over after losing RMX,XXX,XXX"

6. Use the concept of "hope" - "Can I reach my first RM1,000,000 this year?"

Tetapi, mungkin ramai ada masalah dari segi teknik & juga kreativiti.

Teknik pengambilan gambar sesebuah produk mesti dilakukan dengan betul.

Text:

Dengan gambar sebuah produk yang menarik dapat menarik pelanggan akan lebih tertarik dalam membeli sebuah produk. 

Aku akan leraikan 6 sebab kenapa pentingnya gambar produk dalam branding.

Text:

That's why no matter what, first impressions are important.

There has to be a quality and professional picture so that it looks premium.

Text:
3. Gambar produk juga adalah salah satu sebab dapat meningkatkan kepercayaan terhadap brand.

Gambar produk yg baik sangat diperlukan dalam proses untuk branding.

First impression always matter bila kita bercakap tentang branding.

Anda nak customer terus membeli dgn anda kan?
Translated Text:
3. Product pictures are also one of the reasons that can increase trust in the brand.

Good product pictures are very necessary in the branding process.

First impression always matters when we talk about branding.

You want customers to keep buying from you, right?

Text:
4. Lebih mudah bakal pembeli ingat produk anda.

Dengan kata lain, jika pembeli lihat gambar produk  korang, maka mereka akan ingat nama & kegunaan dari produk yang anda jual.

Ini secara dapat membangunkan branding.

This is able to develop branding.

Text:
Manusia ni sibuk dgn kehidupan & tiada masa nak fokus kepada semua iklan.

Kalau iklan korang tak mampu menarik perhatian mereka, maka mereka tak akan baca keseluruhan apa yg korang tulis.

Sebab itu kalau ada masa 15 minit untuk tulis iklan, saya akan spend 10 dekat "HEADLINE".
Translated Text:
People are busy with life & no time to focus on all the ads.

If your ad is not able to attract their attention, then they will not read the whole of what you write.

That's why if I have 15 minutes to write an ad, I will spend 10 near "HEADLINE".

Text:
Ada beberapa cara yang mungkin korang boleh buat.

1. Fokus kepada target audience yang tertentu untuk tarik minat orang tertentu sahaja.

2. Bila menulis, target "pain point" audience korang.

3. Buat headline jenis offer yang buat orang teruja.

Insyaallah akan jadi lebih baik.
Translated Text:
There are several ways you can do it.

1. Focus on a specific target audience to attract the interest of specific people only.

2. When writing, target your audience's "pain point".

3. Make an offer type headline that makes people excited.

God willing it will be better.

Bukan branding tak payah buat terus, cuma fokus lebih kepada menjual.

Text:
Kesilapan yang aku selalu nampak bila orang baru berniaga ni adalah:

- Bila sales kurang,
- Bila tak ramai bertanya,
- Tak banyak prospek bertukar jadi pelanggan,

firasat dorang terus suruh turunkan harga atau tukar produk.

Betul tak?
Translated Text:
The mistakes I always see when people are new to this business are:

- When sales are low,
- When not many people ask,
- Not many prospects turn into customers,

hunch you keep asking to lower the price or change the product.

Right?

Text:
"Tak ramai yang nak beli ni, kena la rendahkan harga supaya dorang pilih aku".

"Competitors aku letak harga 5X.XX, maksudnya harga aku mahal dalam market".

Mungkin soalan ni ada dalam fikiran korang kan?

Teruskan membaca kalau nak tahu lebih lanjut.
Translated Text:
"Not many people want to buy this, I have to lower the price so that people choose me".

"My competitors put a price of 5X.XX, which means my price is expensive in the market".

Maybe this question is in your mind right?

Continue reading if you want to know more.

Text:
The truth is kalau korang rasa turunkan harga adalah idea yang bernas atau "strategik", yang sebenarnya cara turunkan harga ni adalah taktik yang nak menyenangkan kerja.

Kenapa aku cakap macam ni?

Kita cepat rasa takut dan juga nak kerja mudah untuk dapatkan sesuatu.
Translated Text:
The truth is that if you think lowering the price is a smart or "strategic" idea, the actual way to lower the price is a tactic to make work more enjoyable.

Why am I saying this?

We are quick to feel fear and also want to work easily to get something.

Text:
- Lebih senang nak turunkan harga dari naikkan harga.
- Lebih senang nak menjual dan close kalau harga rendah.
- Lebih senang nak buat comparison dengan pelanggan dari competitors yang harga lebih tinggi.

Being comfortable will make you stuck.
Translated Text:
- It's easier to lower prices than increase prices.
- It's easier to sell and close if the price is low.
- It's easier to make comparisons with customers from competitors who have higher prices.

Being comfortable will make you stuck.

Text:
Ada cara nak dapat results dengan tak perlu rendahkan harga.

- Tengok balik macam mana korang positioning kan benefits of your product.

- Pastikan benefits korang tu clear dan mudah faham.

- Backup dengan social proof atau case studies.

Sambungan...
Translated Text:
There is a way to get results without having to lower the price.

- Look back at how you are positioning the benefits of your product.

- Make sure your benefits are clear and easy to understand.

- Backup with social proof or case studies.

Connection...

Text:
- Lebihkan tengok data dari tengok harga. Apa masalah yang korang hadapi. Masalah closing ke? Masalah leads ke?

- Buat survey kepada yang belum membeli. Jadikan ia sebagai rujukan untuk korang tajamkan lagi skills dalam closing the deal.
Translated Text:
- Look at the data more than the price. What problems are you facing? Closing problem? Leads problem?

- Make a survey for those who haven't bought yet. Make it a reference for you to sharpen your skills in closing the deal.

Text:
Ini adalah kerja yang perlu anda buat untuk betulkan masalah sales anda.

Tapi, tak ramai nak buat sebab benda ni perlukan kerja yang banyak.

Ramai yang nak jalan pintas.

Ingat: Orang akan membeli jika ada "value". Bukan harga sahaja menjadi penghalang.

Sekian.
Translated Text:
This is the work you need to do to fix your sales problem.

But, not many people want to do it because this thing needs a lot of work.

Many people want to take a shortcut.

Remember: People will buy if there is "value". Not only price is a barrier.

So much.

Text:
I am stuck between 14.7k to 14.8k.

Bila la nak ke 15k pulak haha.
Translated Text:
I am stuck between 14.7k to 14.8k.

When do you want to go to 15k haha?

Text:
Kenapa terbinanya FAMOUZ Academy ni?

Well, dalam experience aku dah banyak bantu bisnes dalam membuat service marketing kami. 

Tapi, kami tak mampu nak mengajar orang yang nak belajar mengenai pengiklanan secara online ini.

Jadi, di sinilah di mana kami ingin membantu anda. https://t.co/0EeqbZXLeW
Translated Text:
Why was this FAMOUZ Academy built?

Well, in my experience I have helped many businesses in making our marketing service.

But, we are unable to teach people who want to learn about online advertising.

So, this is where we want to help you. https://t.co/0EeqbZXLeW

Text:
Platform ini sesuai untuk:-

1. Founder
2. Agent/stokis/dropship
3. Newbie digital marketing
4. Marketer yang nak tingkatkan skills
5. Fresh graduate

Dan ramai lagi. Nak list ramai tapi tak cukup satu tweet ni.

Macam manakah FAMOUZ Academy ini berfungsi?
Translated Text:
This platform is suitable for:-

1. Founder
2. Agent/stockist/dropship
3. Newbie digital marketing
4. Marketers who want to improve their skills
5. Fresh graduates

And many more. I want to list many but this one tweet is not enough.

How does FAMOUZ Academy work?

Text:
Basically it's an online learning platform di mana anda semua boleh belajar secara sendiri.

Tidak kira di mana, masa dan bila.

Janji ada laptop dan internet sahaja.

Platform ini disediakan untuk anda yang sentiasa busy. Sesuai untuk self-pace learning.
Translated Text:
Basically it's an online learning platform where you can all learn on your own.

No matter where, when and when.

Promise to have a laptop and internet only.

This platform is provided for those of you who are always busy. Suitable for self-paced learning.

Text:
Disebabkan inisiatif bendera putih ini, kami cuba untuk bantu anda yang nak sangat belajar.

Ini sahaja cara yang mampu kami buat untuk bantu anda!

Kami faham ada yang ada masalah dengan situasi sekarang ni. Sekarang ni jugalah masa untuk anda tingkatkan skill!
Translated Text:
Because of this white flag initiative, we try to help you who really want to learn.

This is the only way we can help you!

We understand that there is a problem with the current situation. Now is the time for you to improve your skills!

Text:
Dan anda tak perlu risau, most of the sharing, courses and ebook adalah PERCUMA.

YES BETUL TU!

Kami baru je upload 11 content dan akan menyusul lagi topik-topik yang lain.

YES THAT'S RIGHT!

We have just uploaded 11 content and will follow with other topics.

There will also be a paid course but we reduce it because we want to help you! https://t.co/vMDWFkiZ8P
