Text:
1. Optimize Target Audience

Katakan anda dah buat iklan anda seminggu dan anda tak nampak data yang baik. 

Anda dah buat content yang padu, tetapi orang tidak berminat dengan iklan anda

Kunci untuk menang perang adalah bermula dengan strategi yang baik. Sama juga macam FB Ads
Translated Text:
1. Optimize Target Audience

Let's say you've been running your ad for a week and you're not seeing good data.

You have created solid content, but people are not interested in your ads

The key to winning a war is to start with a good strategy. Same as FB Ads

Text:
Satu perkara yang anda kena faham adalah anda menjual kepada "manusia". 

Sekiranya anda tidak berjaya target orang yang tepat, maka content yang padu tidak akan menarik perhatian mereka.

Target audience adalah "king" dalam optimize Facebook Ads.
Translated Text:
One thing you have to understand is that you are selling to "people".

If you don't manage to target the right people, then cohesive content will not attract their attention.

Target audience is "king" in optimizing Facebook Ads.

Text:
- Siapa pelanggan anda? 
- Apa minat dan kehendak mereka?

Jadi salah satu cara terbaik adalah, Retargeting. Facebook Pixel boleh menarik minat target audience anda semula dengan iklan yang serupa. https://t.co/ZOG9kuCEOn
Translated Text:
- Who are your customers?
- What are their interests and wishes?

So one of the best ways is, Retargeting. Facebook Pixel can re-engage your target audience with similar ads. https://t.co/ZOG9kuCEOn

Text:
Selain itu, boleh gunakan juga Custom Audience.

Orang yang pernah ada minat dengan buat sesuatu dengan iklan anda.

2 perkara ini adalah penting dalam optimize audience anda yang mungkin dah tepu.
Translated Text:
In addition, you can also use Custom Audience.

People who have had an interest in doing something with your ad.

These 2 things are important in optimizing your audience which may be saturated.

Text:
2. Strukturkan Ad Campaign

Facebook membolehkan anda memilih dari 11 jenis objective campaign yang sesuai dengan matlamat perniagaan anda.

Contoh: "Conversion".

Conversion adalah funnel terakhir & paling sukar.

Jadi, kena sentiasa bersedia dengan optimization yang baru.
Translated Text:
2. Structure the Ad Campaign

Facebook allows you to choose from 11 types of objective campaigns that suit your business goals.

Example: "Conversion".

Conversion is the last funnel & most difficult.

So, always be ready with new optimization.

Text:
Jangan fokus dekat 1 campaign sahaja.

Buat diversification. Create your funnel.

Jangan sebab nak aim sales, pilih conversion sahaja.

Anda sendiri kena faham funnel anda dalam berniaga.

Selain itu, gunakan split testing sebagai penentu iklan berjaya atau tidak.
Translated Text:
Don't focus on just 1 campaign.

Make diversification. Create your funnel.

Don't because you want to aim for sales, just choose conversion.

You yourself have to understand your funnel in business.

In addition, use split testing to determine whether or not the ad is successful.

Text:
3. Track Metrics

Untuk nampak "purchase" dalam website, anda perlu pasang Facebook Pixel.

Pixel ini boleh dapat di Facebook Ads Manager anda.

Wajib untuk pasang pixel ini untuk memudahkan komunikasi antara website anda dan iklan di Facebook anda. https://t.co/Lcsk0nNMIh
Translated Text:
3. Track Metrics

To see "purchase" on the website, you need to install Facebook Pixel.

This pixel can be found in your Facebook Ads Manager.

It is mandatory to install this pixel to facilitate communication between your website and your Facebook ad. https://t.co/Lcsk0nNMIh

Text:
Facebook Pixel inilah yang memberi anda semua data dari iklan anda yang ingin dilihat.

Ada 9 specific actions yang boleh anda track dengan Facebook Pixel selain untuk website visitors.

Lihat gambar di bawah untuk faham lebih lanjut. https://t.co/Zb7kGVUjqp
Translated Text:
The Facebook Pixel is what gives you all the data from your ad that you want to see.

There are 9 specific actions that you can track with Facebook Pixel in addition to website visitors.

See the picture below to understand more. https://t.co/Zb7kGVUjqp

Text:
4. Ad Creative

Untuk dapatkan perhatian setiap audience, perlu ada creative dan copy yang menarik.

Selalunya, video perform lebih baik daripada gambar. Tapi tidak semestinya video perform better, video convert better.

Tidak juga. Kena selalu testing content sendiri.
Translated Text:
4. Ad Creative

To get the attention of every audience, there needs to be creative and interesting copy.

Usually, videos perform better than pictures. But the video doesn't have to perform better, the video converts better.

Not really. You have to always test the content yourself.

Text:
5. Monitoring

Walaupun iklan berjalan secara automatik, anda sentiasa perlu pantau iklan anda.

Pantau iklan anda lebih kepada metrik dan progression.

Tutup iklan  yang tak perform dan biarkan iklan yang perform berjalan.
Translated Text:
5. Monitoring

Although ads run automatically, you should always monitor your ads.

Monitor your ads more on metrics and progression.

Close the non-performing ads and let the performing ads run.

Text:
Selain itu Facebook Ads juga ada "Learning Phase".

Algorithm Facebook memerlukan masa untuk tahu siapa yang dapat iklan anda untuk mendapatkan results yang lebih baik.

Iklan yang baru biasanya memerlukan lebih masa untuk lengkapkan "Learning Phase".
Translated Text:
In addition, Facebook Ads also have a "Learning Phase".

Facebook's algorithm needs time to know who gets your ad to get better results.

New ads usually need more time to complete the "Learning Phase".

Text:
Learning Phase yang dah lengkap masanya usually akan dapat momentum yang baik.

Tidak ada formula rahsia untuk dapat pelanggan, Facebook Ads berfungsi dengan baik.

Anda hanya perlu pandai optimize iklan anda.

Harap bermanfaat sharing kali ini.

Terima kasih! https://t.co/j6FxxhAtjP
Translated Text:
Learning Phase that has completed its time will usually get a good momentum.

There is no secret formula to get customers, Facebook Ads work well.

You just need to be good at optimizing your ads.

Please share this time.

Thank you! https://t.co/j6FxxhAtjP

Text:
Mungkin anda sedang mencari sales.

Dan mungkin ada sedang mencari kaedah untuk membuat strategi yang berkesan untuk dapatkan sales.

"The function of a marketing strategy is to describe the purpose behind why you do what you do for your business."
Translated Text:
Maybe you're looking for sales.

And maybe someone is looking for a method to create an effective strategy to get sales.

"The function of a marketing strategy is to describe the purpose behind why you do what you do for your business."

Text:
Marketing strategy adalah 'apa yang akan anda lakukan', dan marketing tactics adalah 'bagaimana anda akan melakukannya'.

Tanpa marketing strategy, mungkin anda sendiri pun tak tahu apa yang anda buat yang betul atau salah.

"Strategy is the foundation of everything!"
Translated Text:
Marketing strategy is 'what will you do', and marketing tactics is 'how will you do it'.

Without a marketing strategy, maybe you yourself don't even know what you are doing is right or wrong.

"Strategy is the foundation of everything!"

Text:
4 strategi utama yang akan aku kongsikan ni insyaallah dapat membantu anda membuat marketing strategy yang berkesan yang dapat…

- tingkatkan sales anda,
- tingkatkan ROI anda

Dan banyak lagi!

Apakah 4 strategi utama tu? Let's dig in!
Translated Text:
The 4 main strategies that I will share, God willing, can help you create an effective marketing strategy that can...

- increase your sales,
- increase your ROI

And many more!

What are the 4 main strategies? Let's dig in!

Text:
1. Set Specific Goals

Bila buat marketing strategy, anda perlu tetapkan goals yang perlu anda capai.

Perkara paling penting yang perlu diingat bila set specific goals adalah anda harus spesifik.

Apa yang anda harap dapat dicapai dengan marketing anda?
Translated Text:
1. Set Specific Goals

When making a marketing strategy, you need to set goals that you need to achieve.

The most important thing to remember when setting specific goals is that you must be specific.

What do you hope to achieve with your marketing?

Text:
Dengan ini, anda juga mungkin kena buat short-term goals dan long-term goals untuk marketing strategy anda.

Gunakan nombor, taktik, dan banyak lagi untuk dapatkan results untuk usaha anda.

Lagi spesifik, lagi bagus.

Contoh: Saya nak RM30,000 sebulan.
Translated Text:
With this, you may also have to make short-term goals and long-term goals for your marketing strategy.

Use numbers, tactics, and more to get results for your efforts.

The more specific, the better.

Example: I want RM30,000 a month.

Text:
2. Identify Your Target Audience

Antara langkah yg penting dalam marketing strategy, untuk bina brand & tingkatkan sales.

Fahami pelanggan yang ideal sangat penting untuk marketing strategy anda.

"It tells you exactly who you are targeting and how to create your content."
Translated Text:
2. Identify Your Target Audience

Among the important steps in marketing strategy, to build a brand & increase sales.

Understanding the ideal customer is very important for your marketing strategy.

"It tells you exactly who you are targeting and how to create your content."

Text:
Ini akan membantu anda menjawab soalan seperti:

- Platform yang digunakan oleh mereka?
- Berapa harga yang sanggup mereka bayar?
- Apa hobi mereka?
- Apa yang mendorong mereka untuk membeli?

"The better you understand the person you are trying to target, the easier your job."
Translated Text:
This will help you answer questions like:

- What platforms do they use?
- How much are they willing to pay?
- What are their hobbies?
- What motivates them to buy?

"The better you understand the person you are trying to target, the easier your job."

Text:
3. Identify Your Competition

Ini dilakukan secara tradisional melalui "competitor analysis".

Competitor Analysis berlaku semasa anda menilai kekuatan dan kelemahan pesaing anda.

Semua orang berada dalam persaingan, jadi penting untuk mengetahui syarikat mana yang sama dgn anda
Translated Text:
3. Identify Your Competition

This is traditionally done through "competitor analysis".

Competitor Analysis occurs when you evaluate the strengths and weaknesses of your competitors.

Everyone is in competition, so it's important to know which companies are the same as you

Text:
Ini dapat membantu anda plan strategi atau taktik apa yang digunakan oleh persaingan yang dapat anda gunakan.

Atau mungkin anda nampak sesuatu yang tidak dilakukan oleh pesaing anda.

Jadi, anda tidak melakukan kesalahan yang sama.

Terdapat 3 jenis pesaing utama:
Translated Text:
This can help you plan what strategy or tactics your competition is using.

Or maybe you see something that your competitors don't.

So, you don't make the same mistake.

There are 3 main types of competitors:

Text:
- Direct competitors

Ini adalah syarikat yang menawarkan produk/servis yang sama dan target audience yang sama dengan anda.

Mereka juga akan mempunyai business models yang serupa dengan anda.

Jadi, ini adalah Direct Competitors.
Translated Text:
- Direct competitors

This is a company that offers the same product/service and the same target audience as you.

They will also have business models similar to yours.

So, these are Direct Competitors.

Text:
- Indirect competitors

Ini adalah syarikat yang mempunyai "pain point" yg mereka cuba selesaikan untuk target audience yg sama dengan anda.

Tetapi, mereka menjual pelbagai produk/servis.

Contoh, kalau kedai makanan laut. Indirect competitor mungkin boleh jadi restoran sushi.
Translated Text:
- Indirect competitors

This is a company that has a "pain point" that they are trying to solve for the same target audience as you.

But, they sell various products/services.

For example, if a seafood shop. An indirect competitor may be a sushi restaurant.

Text:
- Replacement competitors

Syarikat ini tidak menjual produk yang sama dengan anda dan tidak berada dalam industri yang sama.

Tapi, audience anda mungkin ada pilihan untuk beli dari mereka.

"By doing a competitor analysis, you want to identify what your competitive edge is."
Translated Text:
- Replacement competitors

These companies do not sell the same products as you and are not in the same industry.

However, your audience may have the option to buy from them.

"By doing a competitor analysis, you want to identify what your competitive edge is."

Text:
Anda perlu mengenalpasti perkara yang membezakan syarikat anda dari competitors anda.

- Bagaimana anda boleh menonjolkan diri?

- Apakah perkara yang tidak dilakukan oleh pesaing anda yang boleh anda lakukan?

- Apa yang membuat syarikat anda berbeza?
Translated Text:
You need to identify what differentiates your company from your competitors.

- How can you stand out?

- What can you do that your competitors aren't doing?

- What makes your company different?

Text:
4. Choose The Most Effective Platform

"When creating your marketing strategy, choose platforms based on where your target demographic spends the majority of their time."

Jika anda sudah mempunyai database yang cukup besar, mungkin Facebook Ads berkesan untuk anda.
Translated Text:
4. Choose The Most Effective Platform

"When creating your marketing strategy, choose platforms based on where your target demographic spends the majority of their time."

If you already have a large enough database, maybe Facebook Ads will work for you.

Text:
Sebab dalam Facebook Ads, anda boleh upload keseluruhan database email list anda ke Facebook.

- retarget mereka  dan bawa kembali ke website anda

- buat Lookalike Audience

Lookalike Audience adalah tempat Facebook mencari audience baru seperti pelanggan anda yang sedia ada.
Translated Text:
Because in Facebook Ads, you can upload your entire email list database to Facebook.

- retarget them and bring them back to your website

- create a Lookalike Audience

Lookalike Audience is where Facebook finds new audiences like your existing customers.

Text:
Itulah 4 tips dalam membuat marketing strategy yang berkesan!

Seperti biasa, jika anda rasa topik ini berguna, jangan malu untuk RT dan share kepada rakan-rakan peniaga anda.

Terima kasih kerana masih follow thread ini! https://t.co/5VdMzn9etv
Translated Text:
That's 4 tips in making an effective marketing strategy!

As always, if you find this topic useful, don't be shy to RT and share it with your fellow traders.

Thank you for still following this thread! https://t.co/5VdMzn9etv

Translated Text:
The business world has changed dramatically with the use of all modern technologies that are now available for business or personal use.

The biggest change is the way people communicate.

Communication has always played an important role in business. https://t.co/PJndVMcaaI

Text:
Komunikasi sentiasa memainkan peranan penting dalam daily task dan juga dalam berniaga.

Kemajuan teknologi telah merevolusikan cara orang berkomunikasi.

Dari guna telegram ke telefon ke email ke text message sampai la sekarang orang masih gunakan untuk medium komunikasi.
Translated Text:
Communication always plays an important role in daily tasks and also in business.

Advances in technology have revolutionized the way people communicate.

From using telegram to phone to email to text message until now people still use it as a medium of communication.

Text:
Kini brand yang kuat mesti cari cara untuk memuaskan dan terus berhubung dengan pelanggan.

Ini kerana mereka ingin sentiasa tetap berada di fikiran pelanggan.

Brand yang dah kuat takut akan kehilangan kepercayaan pelanggan dan pergi ke pesaing.
Translated Text:
Now strong brands must find ways to satisfy and stay in touch with customers.

This is because they want to always remain in the minds of customers.

Strong brands are afraid of losing customer trust and going to competitors.

Text:
Social Media tidak pernah dirancang untuk tujuan business.

Popularity social media telah menjadi main channel untuk syarikat gunakan sebagai platform untuk marketing.

Mari kita lihat 4 cara yg memainkan peranan penting dalam mengembangkan komunikasi perniagaan di social media.
Translated Text:
Social Media was never designed for business purposes.

The popularity of social media has become a main channel for companies to use as a platform for marketing.

Let's look at 4 ways that play an important role in developing business communication on social media.

Text:
1. Connections

Brand yang kuat selalu memberi tumpuan untuk berinteraksi dgn pelanggan daripada menjual.

Mereka sentiasa tunjuk content yg lebih valuable daripada hard-selling.

Kenapa?

Mereka faham yg membina hubungan dgn pelanggan sangat penting untuk berkembang lebih baik.
Translated Text:
1. Connections

Strong brands always focus on interacting with customers rather than selling.

They always show content that is more valuable than hard-selling.

Why?

They understand that building relationships with customers is very important to grow better.

Text:
2. Campaigning

Dengan adanya social media page, seumpama macam ada broadcasting network anda sendiri.

Dulu, orang ragu-ragu untuk berkongsi pengalaman dgn produk yang dibeli.

Tengok sekarang, sekejap je dah boleh viral. Kalau baik, bagus la. Tapi, kalau tidak...
Translated Text:
2. Campaigning

With a social media page, it's like having your own broadcasting network.

In the past, people were hesitant to share their experiences with the products they bought.

Look now, it can go viral in no time. If it's good, it's good. But, if not...

Text:
Ini memberi peluang kepada syarikat untuk mengembangkan kepercayaan di kalangan pelanggan dengan memberi respond pelanggan serta-merta.

Kalau ada je keluar dekat social media, usually business cepat je respond sebab nak jaga nama baik.
Translated Text:
This gives the company an opportunity to develop trust among customers by providing instant customer response.

If there is something that comes out on social media, usually the business is quick to respond because they want to maintain a good name.

Text:
3. Image

Pelanggan akan mempunyai rasa "sense of belonging" bila dia dah percaya sesuatu brand.

Jadi, image brand di social media perlulah dijaga dengan rapi.

Dari logo sampai la ke design post mestilah nampak premium supaya anda dapat increasekan trust & loyalty mereka.
Translated Text:
3. Image

Customers will have a "sense of belonging" when they trust a brand.

So, the brand image on social media needs to be carefully maintained.

From the logo to the post design, it must look premium so that you can increase trust & their loyalty

Text:
"It is five times cheaper for a business to keep a customer rather than gain customers."

Memang tak mudah untuk cari pelanggan baru.

Tapi, nak kekalkan pelanggan sedia adalah lebih mudah dan lebih murah.
Translated Text:
"It is five times cheaper for a business to keep a customer rather than gain customers."

It's not easy to find new customers.

However, keeping existing customers is easier and cheaper.

Text:
4. Availability

Social media tidak pernah ada masa untuk tidur. Orang ramai menuju ke platform ini dengan cepat. 

Tapi, "Reaching customers isn’t always an easy task."

Sebab tu social media ni tersedia 24/7/365 untuk audience anda.

Bahasa lain dia, "A place that never sleeps"
Translated Text:
4. Availability

Social media never sleeps. Crowds headed to this platform quickly.

But, "Reaching customers isn't always an easy task."

That's why social media is available 24/7/365 for your audience.

His other language, "A place that never sleeps"

Text:
Hari ini, saya nak bantu anda mengenal pasti kenapa Facebook Ads anda tidak berfungsi dan macam mana nak betulkan.

Mula-mula, anda kena tanya 5 soalan ini untuk fahamkan kenapa Facebook Ads anda tak berkesan.

Soalan ni, kena jawab dengan jujur. https://t.co/cwPuIe5IdF
Translated Text:
Today, I want to help you identify why your Facebook Ads are not working and how to fix them.

First, you have to ask these 5 questions to understand why your Facebook Ads are not effective.

This question must be answered honestly. https://t.co/cwPuIe5IdF

Text:
Soalan # 1: Berapa banyak yang anda belanjakan untuk Facebook Ads?

Dan berapa lama dah jalan Facebook Ads anda tu?

Ramai orang tidak melihat hasil yang mereka mahukan dari Facebook kerana letak budget yang terlalu rendah.

Letak RM200 sebulan dan expect dapat RM10,000 in return https://t.co/0BfSRv3gQC
Translated Text:
Question #1: How much are you spending on Facebook Ads?

And how long have your Facebook Ads been running?

Many people do not see the results they want from Facebook because the budget is too low.

Put RM200 a month and expect to get RM10,000 in return https://t.co/0BfSRv3gQC

Text:
Perbelanjaan Facebook Ads anda pun menjadi faktor utama.

Lagi banyak anda spend, lagi banyak traffic anda akan dapat.

Sekiranya anda tidak dapat traffic yang mencukupi, anda mungkin tidak akan dapat hasilkan jumlah yang cukup untuk nampak sales.
Translated Text:
Your Facebook Ads spending is also a major factor.

The more you spend, the more traffic you will get.

If you don't get enough traffic, you may not be able to generate enough to see sales.

Text:
Soalan # 2: Adakah anda menggunakan retargeting di Facebook Ads?

Bila dah dapat traffic, kena la buat sesuatu sebab dah invest banyak dekat Facebook Ads.

Retargeting ni dapat bantu anda.

Kalau takde retargeting, maka campaign Facebook Ads anda mungkin tak perform. https://t.co/WzDABIwwlC
Translated Text:
Question # 2: Do you use retargeting on Facebook Ads?

When you get traffic, you have to do something because you have invested a lot in Facebook Ads.

This retargeting can help you.

If there is no retargeting, then your Facebook Ads campaign may not perform. https://t.co/WzDABIwwlC

Text:
Retargeting adalah proses mengiklankan kepada orang yang sudah ada minat dengan business anda sama ada:

- klik iklan anda
- like iklan anda
- atau masuk website anda

Anda boleh kumpul mereka ini menjadi "retargeting audience" untuk terus tunjuk iklan kepada mereka.
Translated Text:
Retargeting is the process of advertising to people who are already interested in your business either:

- click your ad
- like your ad
- or enter your website

You can gather these people into a "retargeting audience" to continue showing ads to them.

Text:
Fokus bina "retargeting list".

Kalau belum ada list, target untuk dapat 1,000 orang dulu. Lepas dah ada 1,000, target untuk 5,000 orang pula.

Sekiranya anda mempunyai 10,000, boleh la mula buat kempen yang menjual kepada orang-orang ini.

Results insyaallah akan lebih baik.
Translated Text:
Focus on building a "retargeting list".

If there is no list yet, aim to get 1,000 people first. After there are already 1,000, the target is for 5,000 people.

If you have 10,000, you can start a campaign that sells to these people.

Results God willing will be better.

Text:
Soalan # 3: Adakah anda menggunakan Lookalike Audience?

Bila anda dah dapat purchase dari Facebook Ads dan tak buat Lookalike audience ni, serious anda lose banyak dekat sini.

Sama macam retargeting, anda juga boleh buat senarai Lookalike audience ini membeli dengan anda. https://t.co/RlR2PnXGlF
Translated Text:
Question #3: Do you use Lookalike Audience?

If you have been able to purchase from Facebook Ads and do not create a Lookalike audience, you are seriously losing a lot here.

Just like retargeting, you can also create a list of Lookalike audiences to buy with you. https://t.co/RlR2PnXGlF

Text:
Seperti mana nama dia Lookalike audience. 

Facebook Ads akan identify audience yang lebih kurang atau seakan-akan dengan audience yang dah pernah membeli melalui iklan anda.

Facebook Ads akan cari lebih banyak user dengan interest & behaviour yang serupa dengan pelanggan anda.
Translated Text:
Like where is his name Lookalike audience.

Facebook Ads will identify an audience that is more or less similar to an audience that has already purchased through your ad.

Facebook Ads will look for more users with interests & similar behavior to your customers.

Text:
Apa yang best tentang Lookalike audience ni lagi?

Facebook Ads akan cari berjuta-juta orang yang sesuai dengan tingkah laku orang yang sama yang membeli dari anda.

Kalau tak ada purchase lagi, jangan risau. Buat Lookalike audience ni dari apa yang boleh.
Translated Text:
What's the best thing about this Lookalike audience?

Facebook Ads will find millions of people who match the behavior of the same people who buy from you.

If there is no purchase yet, don't worry. Make this Lookalike audience from what you can.

Text:
Boleh create Lookalike audience berdasarkan:

- Visit website
- Add to cart
- Checkout but not purchase
- Video views

Dan banyak lagi.

Anda mungkin akan melihat hasil yang lebih baik dengan membuat Lookalike Audience daripada orang yang pernah purchase dengan anda.
Translated Text:
You can create Lookalike audiences based on:

- Visit websites
- Add to cart
- checkout but no purchase
- Video views

And much more.

You'll likely see better results creating a Lookalike Audience than someone you've purchased with.

Text:
Soalan # 4: Adakah anda buat testing untuk iklan anda?

Berapa banyak iklan yang anda jalankan pada masa yang sama?

Kalau satu je, memang susah nak buat comparison.

Inilah di mana A/B testing atau split test anda kena buat. https://t.co/vqZ7rTb5Cp
Translated Text:
Question # 4: Do you do testing for your ads?

How many ads are you running at the same time?

If it's just one, it's really hard to make a comparison.

This is where A/B testing or split testing you have to do. https://t.co/vqZ7rTb5Cp

Text:
Ini bermaksud anda perlu test:

- Pelbagai jenis gambar
- Headline
- Copywriting

dan banyak lagi untuk menentukan kombinasi mana yang memebuahkan hasil.

Anda tak boleh la buat iklan di Facebook Ads lepas tu expect terus dapat banyak hasil.

Kena monitor performance iklan anda.
Translated Text:
This means you need to test:

- Various types of pictures
- Headlines
- Copywriting

and many more to determine which combinations yield results.

You can't advertise on Facebook Ads and then expect to get a lot of results.

Have to monitor your ad performance.

Text:
Soalan # 5: Apakah funnel sebenar anda?

Funnel adalah proses perjalanan yang akan dilalui oleh audience anda untuk menjadi pelanggan.

Ramai yang akan cuba siarkan satu iklan di Facebook dan berharap orang ramai membeli produk yang bernilai RM1,000. https://t.co/OGa6i4n4Fy
Translated Text:
Question #5: What is your real funnel?

Funnel is the journey process that your audience will go through to become a customer.

Many will try to post an ad on Facebook and hope that people will buy a product worth RM1,000. https://t.co/OGa6i4n4Fy

Text:
That's a "plan to fail" strategy.

Semakin mahal atau rumit produk anda, semakin banyak langkah yang perlu anda lakukan dalam sales funnel anda.

Bina minat audience dengan valuable content atau tawaran. Bawa mereka ke ekosistem anda.
Translated Text:
That's a "plan to fail" strategy.

The more expensive or complex your product is, the more steps you need to go through in your sales funnel.

Build audience interest with valuable content or offers. Bring them into your ecosystem.

Text:
Sekarang perhatikan Facebook Ads anda dan tanyakan pada diri sendiri, "Apakah funnel business aku?"

Kalau anda tak tahu, mungkin itu adalah salah satu punca.

Dan itulah sebab mengapa iklan Facebook anda tidak berfungsi.

Harap sharing kali ini bermanfaat. Terima kasih! https://t.co/zqrfYEgChm
Translated Text:
Now take a look at your Facebook Ads and ask yourself, "What is my business funnel?"

If you don't know, maybe that is one reason.

And that is the reason why your Facebook ads are not working.

Please share this time useful. Thank You! https://t.co/zqrfYEgChm

Text:
Mungkin anda tidak pernah menyangka bahawa 4 Ps berlaku untuk business anda.

Tapi anda kena masukkan 4 Ps ni tak kisah la business anda ni kecil atau tidak.

Kalau tak buat 4 Ps ni, mungkin menjadi sebab company anda tidak grow seperti yang anda nak.
Translated Text:
Maybe you never thought that the 4 Ps apply to your business.

But you have to enter these 4 Ps, it doesn't matter if your business is small or not.

If you don't do these 4 Ps, it might be the reason your company doesn't grow as you want.

Text:
Dengan memahami dan menggunakan 4 Ps, insyaallah dapat bantu business anda.

Saya bahagikan 4 Ps ke dalam format yang mudah difahami supaya anda boleh gunakan untuk kembangkan perniagaan lebih maju.

Tak kira berapa besar atau kecil perniagaan anda, 4 Ps ini sangat penting. https://t.co/UxxpQ52Ge5
Translated Text:
By understanding and using the 4 Ps, God willing can help your business.

I break down the 4 Ps into an easy to understand format that you can use to grow your business further.

No matter how big or small your business is, these 4 Ps are very important. https://t.co/UxxpQ52Ge5

Text:
Every business needs marketing.

Oleh itu, anda perlu memahami 4 Ps marketing ini.

4 Ps ini adalah 
- Product
- Price
- Place
- Promotion.

Jika salah satu dari 4 Ps tidak ada, susah untuk dapat hasil yang baik. https://t.co/1h5RNMLnNC
Translated Text:
Every business needs marketing.

Therefore, you need to understand these 4 Ps of marketing.

4 Ps this is
- Products
-Price
-Place
- Promotions.

If one of the 4 Ps is missing, it is difficult to get good results. https://t.co/1h5RNMLnNC

Text:
Banyak peniaga kecil bersemangat untuk buat promosi tetapi, marketing bukanlah hanya  sekadar promosi semata-mata.

Promosi sebahagian dari marketing...

Tapi jika anda hanya bergantung pada promosi sahaja, anda tidak akan mempunyai strategi yang lengkap.
Translated Text:
Many small business owners are eager to promote, but marketing is not just about promotion.

Promotion is part of marketing...

But if you only rely on promotion, you will not have a complete strategy.

Text:
P yang pertama ialah PRODUCT.

Produk anda adalah produk/servis sebenar yang ingin dijual.

Tanya diri sendiri...

"Adakah saya mempunyai produk yang orang akan beli?" https://t.co/cM1TUzDKFH
Translated Text:
The first P is PRODUCT.

Your product is the actual product/service you want to sell.

Ask yourself...

"Do I have a product that people will buy?" https://t.co/cM1TUzDKFH

Text:
Anda tidak boleh fikir anda mempunyai produk/servis yang bagus atau tidak.

Yang penting ialah sekiranya orang ramai perlukan produk/servis anda atau tidak.

Jadi, apa yang menjadikan produk adalah best product? 

Jawapannya: Yang menyelesaikan masalah sebenar. https://t.co/0WtDo35qK3
Translated Text:
You can't think you have a good product/service or not.

The important thing is if people need your product/service or not.

So, what makes a product the best product?

The answer: That solves the real problem. https://t.co/0WtDo35qK3

Text:
"Masalah" ini boleh menjadi fizikal, mental, atau emosi.

Basically, untuk mengetahui sama ada anda mempunyai produk yang ingin dibeli pengguna bermula dengan mengenal pasti masalah pelanggan tertentu.

Sekiranya produk anda menyelesaikan masalah, lebih mudah untuk convert. https://t.co/cOkogXbRul
Translated Text:
These "problems" can be physical, mental, or emotional.

Basically, to find out if you have a product that consumers want to buy starts with identifying a specific customer problem.

If your product solves a problem, it's easier to convert. https://t.co/cOkogXbRul

Text:
Produk anda harus menyelesaikan masalah sebelum keluar kepada market.

Bila nak pasarkan produk anda, ada dua perkara yang ingin anda pertimbangkan:

1. Masalah apa yang saya selesaikan?
2. Apa yang menjadikan produk saya unik daripada yang ada di pasaran?
Translated Text:
Your product should solve the problem before going to market.

When you want to market your product, there are two things you want to consider:

1. What problem am I solving?
2. What makes my product unique from others on the market?

Text:
P yang kedua ialah PRICE.

Pertanyaan yang ingin anda jawab di sini adalah, "Adakah harga produk saya sesuai?"

Ramai yang tak pasti nak letak harga berapa.

Perkara ini normal untuk yang baru nak mula meniaga.

Jadi, macam mana nak letak harga ni? https://t.co/mk95Ph9ebI
Translated Text:
The second P is PRICE.

The question you want to answer here is, "Is my product priced right?"

Many are not sure what price to put.

This is normal for those who just want to start trading.

So, how do you put this price? https://t.co/mk95Ph9ebI

Text:
Terdapat 4 pricing strategi yang boleh anda pilih:

1. Cost-plus pricing
2. Competitive pricing
3. Value-based pricing
4. Penetration pricing

Apakah maksud-maksud semua ni?
Translated Text:
There are 4 pricing strategies that you can choose from:

1. Cost-plus pricing
2. Competitive pricing
3. Value-based pricing
4. Penetration pricing

What does all this mean?

Text:
1. Cost-plus pricing

Ini adalah kos anda dan mark-up percentage yang anda perlu. 

Cara ini selalunya tidak mengambil kira harga pesaing dan hanya berdasarkan pada kos produk anda dan berapa anda nak markup.

Ecommerce Dropshipers selalu gunakan strategi ni.
Translated Text:
1. Cost-plus pricing

This is your cost and the mark-up percentage you need.

This method usually doesn't take into account competitors' prices and is only based on the cost of your product and how much you want to markup.

Ecommerce Dropshipers always use this strategy.

Text:
2. Competitive pricing

Cara ni tetapkan harga anda berdasarkan apa yang dikenakan oleh pesaing anda.

Cara ini menggunakan pesaing anda sebagai harga "benchmark".

Sebab kadang-kadang kita sendiri tak tahu harga market jadi, mostly akan gunakan cara ini untuk berlawan harga.
Translated Text:
2. Competitive pricing

This way, set your price based on what your competitors are charging.

This method uses your competitors as a "benchmark" price.

Because sometimes we ourselves don't know the market price, so we will mostly use this method to fight the price.

Text:
3. Value-based pricing

Cara ini menetapkan harga anda berdasarkan jumlah yang sanggup dibayar oleh pelanggan anda.

Harga anda mungkin bernilai lebih tinggi, anda tetap memutuskan value-based pricing sebagai penetap harga.

Cara ni, kena ada data dan testimoni sebagai value anda
Translated Text:
3. Value-based pricing

This way you set your price based on what your customers are willing to pay.

Your price may be worth more, you still decide on value-based pricing as the price setter.

This way, you have to have data and testimonials as your value

Text:
4. Penetration pricing

Cara ini anda tetapkan harga rendah dahulu untuk memasuki pasaran yang kompetitif dan naikkan kemudian.

Sales & Marketing adalah tugas yang sangat sukar dan masing-masing memerlukan skill set yang berbeza.

Text:
#1 Time Horizon

Perbezaan terbesar antara marketing & sales adalah waktu yang diperlukan untuk melihat hasilnya.

Dalam sales, anda dapat melihat hasilnya dalam masa 3 bulan.

#1 Time Horizon

The biggest difference between marketing & sales is the time required to see results.

In sales, you can see the results within 3 months.

With marketing, it takes up to 1 year to see good results.

Text:
Tetapi, hasil anda kemungkinan baru nak mula untuk pickup dan potensi dia belum lagi compounding.

Kebanyakan business owner sekarang adalah sales-driven secara semulajadi.

Business owner nak nampak short-term results.
Translated Text:
But, your result is likely to start for pickup and his potential is not yet compounding.

Most business owners now are sales-driven by nature.

Business owners want to see short-term results.

Text:

Marketing pula mungkin susdah nak dapat rentak pada 1st half, kerana marketing bukanlah short-term game sahaja.

Macam Man Utd. 1st half season nampak noob tapi end of season terus no 2.

If the business is football, you might want to lead the table in the 1st half of the season.

Text:
Perlu ingat di sini marketing yang berjaya akan dapat results long-term yang mungkin tidak dapat dicapai dengan mentaliti sales sahaja.

Sales is a numbers game. Marketing is an art.

Sales is a numbers game. Marketing is an art.

Text:
Sales is focused on short-term quotas and results.

Marketing doesn’t care about short-term results. They are playing the long-term game.

Ini sedikit sebanyak tentang time horizon & mindset.

Jom kita ke perbezaan utama yang seterusnya.

Text:

Apa anda rasa bila seseorang terlalu menjual?

Boleh percaya ke orang yang nak menjual tu?

Ramai orang tak suka dipaksa untuk membeli.

Orang lebih suka berurusan dengan orang yang lebih bermaklumat dan lebih berminat untuk menolong anda.

Text:

Aggressive sales are still effective, but the reputation has become bad because this method is no longer effective in the current market.

Text:
#3: Attracting vs. Pursuing

Salespeople must pursue opportunities.

Mereka harus kembangkan senarai prospek untuk mereka close.

Marketing menghasilkan peluang. Strategi marketing yang baik akan ambil perhatian seseorang dan membuat seseorang itu berminat.

They should develop a list of prospects for them to close.

Text:

Jadi, jangan harapkan marketing anda dapat memberikan leads berkualiti kepada perniagaan anda.

Marketing should create an attraction to attract attention.

Text:

Good marketing tells a story. Without a good story, you will not succeed.

Anda perlu menceritakan seseorang yang mempunyai masalah dan cara menghilangkan masalah itu.

Seperti yang saya bagitahu tadi, marketing and storytelling is an art.

Text:

Perbualan biasanya dimulakan dengan jurujual mengemukakan soalan kepada prospek.

Sales, on the other hand, is less about stories and more about asking questions than telling stories.

The conversation usually starts with the salesperson posing a question to the prospect.

Text:
“What are your goals?”

“What have you done so far to reach them?”

“What is reaching your goals worth to you?”

“What are you willing to do about?”

Great salespeople sell by asking, not by telling.

Anda perlu ada kemahiran mendengar kepada setiap orang yang berbeza sifat.

Dalam sales, kebanyakan orang membeli dari orang yang mereka suka dan percayai.

Marketing pula tidak semestinya memerlukan seseorang sebagai frontliner untuk dapatkan sales.

Good marketing can sell your product

Good marketing can sell your product

Text:

Ramai orang menggunakan hashtag dan keywords untuk consume content yang mereka mahu sahaja.

Anda perlu mengetahui apa yang orang cari. https://t.co/2NtNISTtLx
Translated Text:
On social media, one of the most popular ways to reach people for free is by using the right hashtag.

Many people use hashtags and keywords to consume only the content they want.

You need to know what people are looking for. https://t.co/2NtNISTtLx

Text:
Sekiranya anda memudahkan orang mencari content anda, dan anda banyak post content secara konsisten, maka anda akan terus meningkatkan visibility business anda.

Tetapi kena ingat, visibility secara organik atau percuma adalah proses yang perlahan.
Translated Text:
If you make it easy for people to find your content, and you post a lot of content consistently, then you will continue to increase the visibility of your business.

But remember, organic or free visibility is a slow process.

Text:
Jika anda mempunyai budget untuk dibelanjakan untuk iklan, ia akan mempercepatkan proses.

Platform seperti YouTube, Facebook, Google, Instagram semuanya mempunyai platform iklan yang anda boleh promosikan.

Ini akan membantu anda reach lebih banyak orang dengan lebih cepat. https://t.co/HfFU3Fm4Ip
Translated Text:
If you have a budget to spend on advertising, it will speed up the process.

Platforms like YouTube, Facebook, Google, Instagram all have ad platforms that you can promote.

This will help you reach more people faster. https://t.co/HfFU3Fm4Ip

Text:
Stage 3: Marketing Funnel

Jadi, anda dah ada visibility. Apa anda perlu buat?

Anda dah ada beribu-ribu followers dan ramai yang suka content anda.

TETAPI, itu tidak bermakna mereka akan membeli dari anda.
Translated Text:
Stage 3: Marketing Funnel

So, you already have visibility. What do you need to do?

You already have thousands of followers and many like your content.

BUT, that doesn't mean they will buy from you.

Text:
That’s where your marketing funnel comes in.

Jika anda dah baca sampai sini, tadi kita hanya bincangkan tentang building awareness.

Jadi bagaimana anda nak orang ke funnel anda dan betul-betul membeli?

The answer is content, but a certain type of content. https://t.co/ZfYceE7Qk7
Translated Text:
That's where your marketing funnel comes in.

If you've read this far, we just talked about building awareness.

So how do you get people to your funnel and actually buy?

The answer is content, but a certain type of content. https://t.co/ZfYceE7Qk7

Text:
Anda perlu share content yang lebih specific yang membina interest terhadap apa yang anda jual.

Anda mungkin berkongsi:

- Customer reviews
- Case studies
- What makes your business unique
- Benefits of the products or services yang anda jual https://t.co/4aDd0O8Xn6
Translated Text:
You need to share more specific content that builds interest in what you are selling.

You may share:

- Customer reviews
- Case studies
- What makes your business unique
- Benefits of the products or services that you sell https://t.co/4aDd0O8Xn6

Text:
Sekiranya anda tidak berkongsi apa impak produk/servis anda kepada pelanggan anda, mereka ada pilihan untuk pilih produk/servis lain.

Jadi apa nak kena share ni?

Well kami suggest anda untuk ada 3 segmen yang berbeza.
Translated Text:
If you don't share the impact of your product/service on your customers, they have the option to choose another product/service.

So what do you want to share?

Well we suggest you to have 3 different segments.

Text:
Segmen content anda kepada 3 kumpulan:

1. Top of Funnel – These are the people who are becoming aware of your business

2. Middle of Funnel – These are the engaged people that you want to sell to

3.Bottom of Funnel – These are people who are actively considering your business
Translated Text:
Segmen content anda kepada 3 kumpulan:

1. Top of Funnel – These are the people who are becoming aware of your business

2. Middle of Funnel – These are the engaged people that you want to sell to

3.Bottom of Funnel – These are people who are actively considering your business

Text:
Setiap segmen ini memerlukan content yang berbeza.

Contohnya, anda mungkin buat content Top Of Funnel untuk membina brand awareness di social media.

Anda mungkin boleh offer sesuatu yang percuma, untuk capture leads. Ini bagus untuk Middle Of Funnel.
Translated Text:
Each of these segments requires different content.

For example, you might create Top Of Funnel content to build brand awareness on social media.

You may be able to offer something free, to capture leads. This is great for Middle Of Funnel.

Text:
Dan akhirnya, anda mungkin mempunyai plan untuk buat iklan retargeting dengan specific content untuk Bottom Of Funnel.

Ingat, untuk buat content secara jayanya, anda mesti mempunyai content yang berkualiti, visibility tinggi, dan marketing funnel yang tepat.

Harap bermanfaat. https://t.co/yZOuoeArQx
Translated Text:
And finally, you may have a plan to create retargeting ads with specific content for Bottom Of Funnel.

Remember, to create content successfully, you must have quality content, high visibility, and the right marketing funnel.

Hope useful. https://t.co/yZOuoeArQx

Text:
Dulu, Facebook panggil "Ad Relevance Score".

Lagi 2 ad relevance diagnostic adalah:

- Engagement rate ranking
- Conversion rate ranking

Jadi, bagaimana Facebook Quality Ranking Score mempengaruhi prestasi iklan anda?

Follow rapat thread ini dan share kepada yang memerlukan. https://t.co/1mdXlXL8n8
Translated Text:
In the past, Facebook called "Ad Relevance Score".

Two more ad relevance diagnostics are:

- Engagement rate ranking
- Conversion rate ranking

So, how does Facebook's Quality Ranking Score affect your ad's performance?

Follow this thread meeting and share with those who need it. https://t.co/1mdXlXL8n8

Text:
Facebook guna ranking ini untuk menentukan bagaimana iklan anda dibandingkan dengan advertiser lain yang buat iklan kepada audience yang sama.

Memiliki ranking score yang lebih tinggi daripada pesaing anda akan membantu Facebook membuat keputusan untuk keluarkan iklan anda. https://t.co/ULubSdAifI
Translated Text:
Facebook uses this ranking to determine how your ad compares to other advertisers who create ads for the same audience.

Having a higher ranking score than your competitors will help Facebook make the decision to issue your ad. https://t.co/ULubSdAifI

Text:
Inilah sebabnya mengapa mempunyai ranking score yang lebih tinggi usually dapat menurunkan kos anda setiap 1000 impressions (CPM) dan Cost per Click (CPC).

Facebook’s 3 Ad Relevance Diagnostics:

- Quality Ranking Score
- Engagement Rate Ranking
- Conversion Rate Ranking
Translated Text:
This is why having a higher ranking score can usually lower your cost per 1000 impressions (CPM) and Cost per Click (CPC).

Facebook's 3 Ad Relevance Diagnostics:

- Quality Ranking Score
- Engagement Rate Ranking
- Conversion Rate Ranking

Text:
1. Quality Ranking Score

“Ad quality through various signals, such as feedback from people viewing or hiding the ad and assessments of low-quality attributes in the ad, such as withholding information, sensationalized language and engagement bait.”

Tak faham? Tgk contoh dibawah https://t.co/78Nw7OzqTv
Translated Text:
1. Quality Ranking Score

“Ad quality through various signals, such as feedback from people viewing or hiding the ad and assessments of low-quality attributes in the ad, such as withholding information, sensationalized language and engagement bait.”

Tak faham? Tgk contoh dibawah https://t.co/78Nw7OzqTv

Text:
Facebook juga memberikan beberapa contoh visual mengenai perkara yang tidak boleh dilakukan.

Secara ringkas, anda tidak mahu iklan anda kelihatan "spammy" atau menggunakan bahasa yang tidak menarik pembaca untuk klik. https://t.co/vNKE2dLMyF
Translated Text:
Facebook also provides some visual examples of what not to do.

Simply put, you don't want your ad to look "spammy" or use language that doesn't entice readers to click. https://t.co/vNKE2dLMyF

Text:
Penting juga untuk Facebook menganalisis CTA/Landing Page yang akan digunakan untuk pengguna klik.

Facebook tidak hanya berhenti menganalisis iklan anda - where you send your traffic to from your ad does matter.

Sebab tu kena jaga Quality Ranking Score...
Translated Text:
It is also important for Facebook to analyze the CTA/Landing Page that will be used for user clicks.

Facebook doesn't just stop at analyzing your ads - where you send your traffic to from your ad does matter.

That's why you have to maintain the Quality Ranking Score...

Text:
Beberapa perkara yang dianggap oleh Facebook sebagai "low-quality attribute" adalah:

- Misleading experiences,
- Pop-up ads
- Unexpected content experiences

Jadi, jagalah 3 aspek ini untuk mendapat best performance.
Translated Text:
Some of the things that are considered by Facebook as a "low-quality attribute" are:

- Misleading experiences,
- Pop-up ads
- Unexpected content experiences

So, take care of these 3 aspects to get the best performance.

Text:
2. Engagement Rate Ranking

“Calculates the likelihood that a person will click, react to, comment on, share or expand an ad. Engagement-baiting (For example, asking for likes, comments, and so on) will not improve your ad’s performance.”

Translated Text:
2. Engagement Rate Ranking

“Calculates the likelihood that a person will click, react to, comment on, share or expand an ad. Engagement-baiting (For example, asking for likes, comments, and so on) will not improve your ad’s performance.”

Text:
Oleh itu, berhati-hati dalam pengunaan ayat, 'LIKE page ini!' Atau 'Komen di bawah!' Dalam iklan Facebook anda.

Ini kerana Facebook mengatakan bahawa sebenarnya akan menurunkan skor anda.

Anda mahu buat iklan anda secara organik dalam menaikkan Facebook Engagement.
Translated Text:
Therefore, be careful in using the sentence, 'LIKE this page!' Or 'Comment below!' In your Facebook ads.

This is because Facebook says that will actually lower your score.

You want to create your ads organically to increase Facebook Engagement.

Text:
3. Conversion Rate Ranking

“Conversion rate ranking explains how your ad’s expected conversion rate compared to ads with the same optimization goal competing for the same audience...

Translated Text:

Text:
...The expected conversion rate calculates the likelihood that a person who viewed your ad will complete your optimization goal.”

Apabila anda memilih objektif kempen iklan Facebook, anda diberi pilihan untuk dipilih berdasarkan apa objektif anda. https://t.co/Jyig69zw23
Translated Text:
...The expected conversion rate calculates the likelihood that a person who viewed your ad will complete your optimization goal.”

When you choose a Facebook ad campaign objective, you are given the option to choose based on what your objective is. https://t.co/Jyig69zw23

Text:
Contohnya, jika anda ingin tingkatkan engagement anda, anda boleh pilih objektif engagement.

Atau jika anda ingin mendorong lebih banyak website purchase, anda boleh pilih objektif conversion.

Okay bahagian ni akan teknikal sikit. Jadi, kalau tak faham boleh baca balik nanti.
Translated Text:
For example, if you want to increase your engagement, you can choose an engagement objective.

Or if you want to encourage more website purchases, you can choose conversion objectives.

Okay this part will be a little technical. So, if you don't understand, you can read it again later.

Text:
Katakan anda menjual yoga pants, anda pilih: 

- Campaign conversion
- Buat targeting ibu berusia antara 30-55 tahun yang berminat dengan yoga.

Facebook akan compare iklan anda dengan orang lain yang aim audience yang sama.
Translated Text:
Let's say you sell yoga pants, you choose:

- Campaign conversion
- Target mothers aged between 30-55 years old who are interested in yoga.

Facebook will compare your ad with other people who have the same target audience.

Text:
Sekarang mari kita bincangkan mengenai Facebook Scoring System.

Untuk ketiga-tiga skor, Facebook sediakan skor:

- Above Average
- Average
- Below Average (Bottom 35% of ads)
- Below Average (Bottom 20% of ads)
- Below Average (Bottom 10% of ads)
Translated Text:
Now let's talk about the Facebook Scoring System.

For all three scores, Facebook provides scores:

- Above Average
- Average
- Below Average (Bottom 35% of ads)
- Below Average (Bottom 20% of ads)
- Below Average (Bottom 10% of ads)

Text:
Ini dibandingkan dengan iklan lain yang aim audience yang sama seperti anda.

Semakin rendah skor anda, semakin banyak anda perlu membayar untuk reach, impression, dan klik.

Bagaimana Mengetahui Apa Skor Peringkat Kualiti Facebook Anda?

Jom saya ajar!
Translated Text:
This is compared to other ads that aim for the same audience as you.

The lower your score, the more you have to pay for reach, impressions, and clicks.

How to Know What Your Facebook Quality Score Score is?

Let me teach!

Text:

Text:

Text:

Text:
Ramai yang nak jadi content creator bermula dengan TikTok sekarang ni. Sebabnya adalah:-

- Followers cepat naik
- Peluang untuk masuk "FYP". Ini ada kena mengena dengan frequency & watch time.
- Boleh viral bila-bila masa (asalkan consistent & ada unsur ingin tahu dalam content) https://t.co/7b0WvQ7Pvi

Text:
@khairulaming Sebagai mangsa pasca banjir nak cadangkan sumbangan diperlukan:
-sabun serbuk, penyapu, baldi, berus kecik, plastik sampah BESARRR. Mop tak wajibbb tapi penolak air tu fansen
-beras
-pampers&pad
-minyak
-air/lunchpack sbb time cuci dah tak fikir camna lunch dah
Translated Text:
@khairulaming As a post-flood victim, I would like to suggest that donations are needed:
- powder soap, broom, bucket, small brush, BIG garbage plastic. A mop is not mandatory, but the water repellent is a fan
-rice
-pampers & pads
- oil
-water/lunchpack because it's washing time and I don't think about lunch

Text:
sejadah, pakaian, sebelum dia mula jadi keras sbb lumpur. barang2 mcm pinggan mangkuk, tupperware tu last sekali pun takpe

4. kalau ada tilam yg mmg dh berbau teruk and tak boleh pakai, letak dulu depan rumah. pls jangan bakar tilam tu, asap hitam busuk keluar nanti
Translated Text:
mats, clothes, before he started to become hard as mud. Things like tableware, tupperware are not available

4. if there is a mattress that really smells bad and you can't use it, put it in front of the house first. pls don't burn the mattress, black smoke will come out later

Text:
5. keluarkan sampah dari parit depan rumah supaya air cucian boleh mula mengalir

6. kalau nak cat balik dinding and ada duit lebih, invest kat cat minyak. kalau terjadi lg banjir inshaAllah tak melekat sgt “water mark”
Translated Text:
5. remove the garbage from the gutter in front of the house so that the washing water can start flowing

6. if you want to repaint the wall and have more money, invest in oil paint. if there is another flood, inshaAllah, the "water mark" will not stick

Text: 7. actually benda plg tak senang lepas banjir ialah debu dan bau. mmg akan keluar bau bangkai and satu kejiranan akan jd sangat berdebu bila lumpur kering dan mula berkerak. yg ni mmg kena tnggu hujan berkali-kali utk flush balik semua debu. this will take a few weeks
Translated Text: 7. actually the most unpleasant thing after a flood is dust and smell. The smell of carcasses will come out and a neighborhood will become very dusty when the mud dries and starts to crust over. This one has to wait for rain many times to flush back all the dust. this will take a few weeks

Text: 8. yang part electronic, kereta, motor ni aku nk mintak tolong org lain sambung kat bwh cara2 nak handle kalau dh tenggelam air banjir. sbb time banjir teruk dulu aku tengah sekolah lg time tu, tak pandai benda2 macam ni. feel free to add more details guys tqq 🙏🏻
Translated Text: 8. For electronic parts, cars, motorcycles, I want to ask other people to help me on how to handle it if it is submerged in flood water. because when the flood was bad, I was in school at the time, so I'm not good at things like this. feel free to add more details guys tqq 🙏🏻

Text: @khairulaming Kebanyakan barang elektronik/elektrik (fon, peti, tv, lampu, kipas, laptop) tak rosak walaupun terendam dalam air. Barang tu akan akan rosak kalau ada sumber elektrik. Ia akan menyebabkan litar pintas (short circuit). Sebab tu disarankan tutup plug atau buka bateri kalau banjir.
Translated Text: @khairulaming Most electronic/electrical items (phones, boxes, TVs, lamps, fans, laptops) are not damaged even if submerged in water. The item will be damaged if there is an electrical source. It will cause a short circuit. That's why it is recommended to close the plug or open the battery if it floods.

Text:
@khairulaming Kawan aku dia duduk rumah sewa.

Rumah sewa banjir masuk air, besok dia angkat barang lepas tuu blah dan cari sewa rumah lain. 

Tang ni lah baru tahu nikmat nya hidup menyewa rumah berbanding own the house. 

Cuma deposit rumah lah burn.

@khairulaming My friend lives in a rented house.

The rental house is flooded with water, tomorrow he will pick up the stuff and leave it blah and look for another house to rent.

It's only now that I know the joy of living in renting a house compared to owning the house.

Only the house deposit is burned.

Translated Text: @khairulaming If you want to donate/buy a waterjet to clean the flood, buy a brushless/induction motor or one that uses gasoline, it's better. Text:
@khairulaming Additional tips;
1. On lampu kereta time hujan lebat
2. Jangan pasang hazard light (double signal tu).
3. Tukar lane please bg signal.
4. Jaga jarak dgn kenderaan depan.
5. Jangan laju sgt, air bertakung, tayar kurang grip.
6. Jangan slow sgt, punca jammed nanti.

Stay safe!
Translated Text:
@khairulaming Additional tips;
1. Turn on the car lights when it's raining heavily
2. Don't install a hazard light (double signal).
3. Change lanes, please give a signal.
4. Keep your distance from the vehicle in front.
5. Don't go too fast, the water will hold up, the tires won't grip.
6. Don't be too slow, the cause will be jammed later.

stay safe!

Text:
@khairulaming Tip bila memandu dalam hujan
1. On lampu kereta time hujan lebat
2. Jangan pasang hazard light (double signal tu).
3. Tukar lane please bg signal.
4. Jaga jarak dgn kenderaan depan.
5. Jangan laju sgt, air bertakung, tayar kurang grip.
6. Jangan slow sgt, punca jammed nanti.
Translated Text:
@khairulaming Tip when driving in the rain
1. Turn on the car lights when it rains heavily
2. Do not install hazard light (double signal).
3. Change lanes please signal.
4. Keep a distance from the vehicle in front.
5. Don't go too fast, water stagnates, tires lack grip.
6. Don't be very slow, the cause will be jammed later.
